obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (16786)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16786&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Trade Marks Act, 1999.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date ^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint:`
  line
  line `Provided that different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act, and any reference`
  line `in any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to the coming`
  line `into force of that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 . 15th September, 2003, vide notification No. S.O. 1048(E), dated 15th September, 2003, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (16787)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Definitions and interpretation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16787&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line ^1*****
  line
  line `(b) assignment means an assignment in writing by act of the parties concerned;`
  line
  line `(c) associated trade marks means trade marks deemed to be, or required to be, registered as`
  line `associated trade marks under this Act;`
  line
  line ^1*****
  line
  line `(e) certification trade mark means a mark capable of distinguishing the goods or services in`
  line `connection with which it is used in the course of trade which are certified by the proprietor of the`
  line `mark in respect of origin, material, mode of manufacture of goods or performance of services, quality,`
  line `accuracy or other characteristics from goods or services not so certified and registrable as such under`
  line `Chapter IX in respect of those goods or services in the name, as proprietor of the certification trade`
  line `mark, of that person;`
  line
  line ^1*****
  line
  line `(g) collective mark means a trade mark distinguishing the goods or services of members of an`
  line `association of persons (not being a partnership within the meaning of the Indian Partnership`
  line `Act, 1932 (9 of 1932) which is the proprietor of the mark from those of others;`
  line
  line `(h) deceptively similar.A mark shall be deemed to be deceptively similar to another mark if`
  line `it so nearly resembles that other mark as to be likely to deceive or cause confusion;`
  line
  line `(i) false trade description means--`
  line
  line `(I) a trade description which is untrue or misleading in a material respect as regards the goods`
  line `or services to which it is applied; or`
  line
  line `(II) any alteration of a trade description as regards the goods or services to which it is applied,`
  line `whether by way of addition, effacement or otherwise, where that alteration makes the description`
  line `untrue or misleading in a material respect; or`
  line
  line `(III) any trade description which denotes or implies that there are contained, as regards the`
  line `goods to which it is applied, more yards or metres than there are contained therein standard yards`
  line `or standard metres; or`
  line
  line `(IV) any marks or arrangement or combination thereof when applied--`
  line
  line `(a) to goods in such a manner as to be likely to lead persons to believe that the goods are`
  line `the manufacture or merchandise of some person other than the person whose merchandise or`
  line `manufacture they really are;`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to services in such a manner as to be likely to lead persons to believe that`
  line `the services are provided or rendered by some person other than the person whose services`
  line `they really are; or`
  line
  line `(V) any false name or initials of a person applied to goods or services in such manner as if`
  line `such name or initials were a trade description in any case where the name or initials`
  line
  line `(a) is or are not a trade mark or part of a trade mark; and`
  line
  line `(b) is or are identical with or deceptively similar to the name or initials of a person`
  line `carrying on business in connection with goods or services of the same description or both and`
  line `who has not authorised the use of such name or initials; and`
  line
  line `(c) is or are either the name or initials of a fictitious person or some person not bona fide`
  line `carrying on business in connection with such goods or services,`
  line `and the fact that a trade description is a trade mark or part of a trade mark shall not prevent such`
  line `trade description being a false trade description within the meaning of this Act;`
  line
  line `(j) goods means anything which is the subject of trade or manufacture;`
  line
  line ^2*****;
  line
  line `(l) limitations (with its grammatical variations) means any limitation of the exclusive right to`
  line `the use of a trade mark given by the registration of a person as proprietor thereof, including`
  line `limitations of that right as to mode or area of use within India or outside India;`
  line
  line `(m) mark includes a device, brand, heading, label, ticket, name, signature, word, letter,`
  line `numeral, shape of goods, packaging or combination of colours or any combination thereof;`
  line
  line ^2*****
  line
  line `(o) name includes any abbreviation of a name;`
  line
  line `(p) notify means to notify in the Trade Mark Journal published by the Registrar;`
  line
  line `(q) package includes any case, box, container, covering, folder, receptacle, vessel, casket,`
  line `bottle, wrapper, label, band, ticket, reel, frame, capsule, cap, lid, stopper and cork;`
  line
  line `(r) permitted use, in relation to a registered trade mark, means the use of trade mark--`
  line
  line `(i) by a registered user of the trade mark in relation to goods or services--`
  line
  line `(a) with which he is connected in the course of trade; and`
  line
  line `(b) in respect of which the trade mark remains registered for the time being; and`
  line
  line `(c) for which he is registered as registered user; and`
  line
  line `(d) which complies with any conditions or limitations to which the registration of`
  line `registered user is subject; or`
  line
  line `(ii) by a person other than the registered proprietor and registered user in relation to goods or`
  line services--
  line
  line `(a) with which he is connected in the course of trade; and`
  line
  line `(b) in respect of which the trade mark remains registered for the time being; and`
  line
  line `(c) by consent of such registered proprietor in a written agreement; and`
  line
  line `(d) which complies with any conditions or limitations to which such user is subject and to`
  line `which the registration of the trade mark is subject;`
  line
  line `^3[(s) prescribed means,`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to proceedings before a High Court, prescribed by rules made by the High`
  line `Court; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in other cases, prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line ]
  line
  line `(t) register means the Register of Trade Marks referred to in sub-section (1) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(u) registered (with its grammatical variations) means registered under this Act;`
  line
  line `(v) registered proprietor, in relation to a trade mark, means the person for the time being`
  line `entered in the register as proprietor of the trade mark;`
  line
  line `(w) registered trade mark means a trade mark which is actually on the register and remaining in`
  line force;
  line
  line `(x) registered user means a person who is for the time being registered as such under`
  line `section 49;`
  line
  line `(y) Registrar means the Registrar of Trade Marks referred to in section 3;`
  line
  line `(z) Service means service of any description which is made available to potential users and`
  line `includes the provision of services in connection with business of any industrial or commercial matters`
  line `such as banking, communication, education, financing, insurance, chit funds, real estate, transport,`
  line `storage, material treatment, processing, supply of electrical or other energy, boarding, lodging,`
  line `entertainment, amusement, construction, repair, conveying of news or information and advertising;`
  line
  line `(za) trade description means any description, statement or other indication, direct or indirect--,`
  line
  line `(i) as to the number, quantity, measure, gauge or weight of any goods; or`
  line
  line `(ii) as to the standard of quality of any goods or services according to a classification`
  line `commonly used or recognised in the trade; or`
  line
  line `(iii) as to fitness for the purpose, strength, performance or behaviour of any goods, being`
  line `drug as defined in the Drugs and Cosmetics Act, 1940 (23 of 1940), or food as defined in the`
  line `Prevention of Food Adulteration Act, 1954 (37 of 1954); or`
  line
  line `(iv) as to the place or country in which or the time at which any goods or services were made,`
  line `produced or provided, as the case may be; or`
  line
  line `(v) as to the name and address or other indication of the identity of the manufacturer or of the`
  line `person providing the services or of the person for whom the goods are manufactured or services`
  line `are provided; or`
  line
  line `(vi) as to the mode of manufacture or producing any goods or providing services; or`
  line
  line `(vii) as to the material of which any goods are composed; or`
  line
  line `(viii) as to any goods being the subject of an existing patent, privilege or copyright,`
  line `and includes--`
  line
  line `(a) any description as to the use of any mark which according to the custom of the trade is`
  line `commonly taken to be an indication of any of the above matters;`
  line
  line `(b) the description as to any imported goods contained in any bill of entry or shipping bill;`
  line
  line `(c) any other description which is likely to be misunderstood or mistaken for all or any of the`
  line `said matters;`
  line
  line `(zb) trade mark means a mark capable of being represented graphically and which is capable of`
  line `distinguishing the goods or services of one person from those of others and may include shape of`
  line `goods, their packaging and combination of colours; and--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to Chapter XII (other than section 107), a registered trade mark or a mark used`
  line `in relation to goods or services for the purpose of indicating or so as to indicate a connection in`
  line `the course of trade between the goods or services, as the case may be, and some person having the`
  line `right as proprietor to use the mark; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to other provisions of this Act, a mark used or proposed to be used in relation`
  line `to goods or services for the purpose of indicating or so as to indicate a connection in the course of`
  line `trade between the goods or services, as the case may be, and some person having the right, either`
  line `as proprietor or by way of permitted user, to use the mark whether with or without any indication`
  line `of the identity of that person, and includes a certification trade mark or collective mark;`
  line
  line `(zc) transmission means transmission by operation of law, devolution on the personal`
  line `representative of a deceased person and any other mode of transfer, not being assignment;`
  line
  line `(zd) Technical Member means a Member who is not a Judicial Member;`
  line
  line ^4*****
  line
  line `(zg) well known trade mark, in relation to any goods or services, means a mark which has`
  line `become so to the substantial segment of the public which uses such goods or receives such services`
  line `that the use of such mark in relation to other goods or services would be likely to be taken as`
  line `indicating a connection in the course of trade or rendering of services between those goods or services`
  line `and a person using the mark in relation to the first-mentioned goods or services.`
  line
  line `(2) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires, any reference--`
  line
  line `(a) to trade mark shall include reference to collective mark or certification trade mark;`
  line
  line `(b) to the use of a mark shall be construed as a reference to the use of printed or other visual`
  line `representation of the mark;`
  line
  line `(c) to the use of a mark,--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to goods, shall be construed as a reference to the use of the mark upon, or in`
  line `any physical or in any other relation whatsoever, to such goods;`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to services, shall be construed as a reference to the use of the mark as or as part`
  line `of any statement about the availability, provision or performance of such services;`
  line
  line `(d) to the Registrar shall be construed as including a reference to any officer when discharging the`
  line `functions of the Registrar in pursuance of sub-section (2) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(e) to the Trade Marks Registry shall be construed as including a reference to any office of the`
  line `Trade Marks Registry.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of this Act, goods and services are associated with each other if it is likely that`
  line `those goods might be sold or otherwise traded in and those services might be provided by the same`
  line `business and so with descriptions of goods and descriptions of services.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of this Act, existing registered trade mark means a trade mark registered under`
  line `the Trade and Merchandise Marks Act, 1958 (43 of 1958) immediately before the commencement of this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Clauses (a), (d) and (f) omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 21 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Clauses (k) and (n) omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 21 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 21, for clause (s) (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `4. Clauses (ze) and (zf) omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 21 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
