  title `Appointment of Registrar and other officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16788&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, appoint a person to be known as the Controller-General of Patents,`
  line `Designs and Trade Marks, who shall be the Registrar of Trade Marks for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may appoint such other officers with such designations as it thinks fit for`
  line `the purpose of discharging, under the superintendence and direction of the Registrar, such functions of the`
  line `Registrar under this Act as he may from time to time authorise them to discharge.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (16789)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Power of Registrar to withdraw or transfer cases, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16789&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to the generality of`
  line `the provisions of sub-section (2) of section 3, the Registrar may, by order in writing and for reasons to be`
  line `recorded therein, withdraw any matter pending before an officer appointed under the said sub-section (2)`
  line `and deal with such matter himself either de novo or from the stage it was so withdrawn or transfer the`
  line `same to another officer so appointed who may, subject to special directions in the order of transfer,`
  line `proceed with the matter either de novo or from the stage it was so transferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (16790)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Trade Marks Registry and offices thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16790&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of this Act, there shall be a`
  line `trade marks registry and the Trade Marks Registry established under the Trade and Merchandise Marks`
  line `Act, 1958 (43 of 1958) shall be the Trade Marks Registry under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The head office of the Trade Marks Registry shall be at such place as the Central Government`
  line `may specify, and for the purpose of facilitating the registration of trade marks, there may be established at`
  line `such places as the Central Government may think fit branch offices of the Trade Marks Registry.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, define the territorial limits`
  line `within which an office of the Trade Marks Registry may exercise its functions.`
  line
  line `(4) There shall be a seal of the Trade Marks Registry.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (16791)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `The Register of Trade Marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16791&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of this Act, a record called the Register of`
  line `Trade Marks shall be kept at the head office of the Trade Marks Registry, wherein shall be entered all`
  line `registered trade marks with the names, addresses and description of the proprietors, notifications of`
  line `assignment and transmissions, the names, addresses and descriptions of registered users, conditions,`
  line `limitations and such other matter relating to registered trade marks as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), it shall be lawful for the Registrar to keep`
  line `the records wholly or partly in computer floppies diskettes or in any other electronic form subject to such`
  line `safeguards as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Where such register is maintained wholly or partly on computer under sub-section (2) any`
  line `reference in this Act to entry in the Register shall be construed as the reference to any entry as maintained`
  line `on computer or in any other electronic form.`
  line
  line `(4) No notice of any trust, express or implied or constructive, shall be entered in the register and no`
  line `such notice shall be receivable by the Registrar.`
  line
  line `(5) The register shall be kept under the control and management of the Registrar.`
  line
  line `(6) There shall be kept at each branch office of the Trade Marks Registry a copy of the register and`
  line `such of the other documents mentioned in section 148 as the Central Government may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, direct.`
  line
  line `(7) The Register of Trade Marks, both Part A and Part B, existing at the commencement of this Act,`
  line `shall be incorporated in and form part of the register under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (16792)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Classification of goods and services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16792&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Registrar shall classify goods and services, as far`
  line `as may be, in accordance with the International classification of goods and services for the purposes of`
  line `registration of trade marks.`
  line
  line `(2) Any question arising as to the class within which any goods or services falls shall be determined`
  line `by the Registrar whose decision shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (16793)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Publication of alphabetical index.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16793&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Registrar may publish in the prescribed manner an`
  line `alphabetical index of classification of goods and services referred to in section 7.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any goods or services are not specified in the alphabetical index of goods and services`
  line `published under sub-section (1), the classification of goods or services shall be determined by the`
  line `Registrar in accordance with sub-section (2) of section 7.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (16794)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Absolute grounds for refusal of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16794&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The trade marks--`
  line
  line `(a) which are devoid of any distinctive character, that is to say, not capable of distinguishing the`
  line `goods or services of one person from those of another person;`
  line
  line `(b) which consist exclusively of marks or indications which may serve in trade to designate the`
  line `kind, quality, quantity, intended purpose, values, geographical origin or the time of production of the`
  line `goods or rendering of the service or other characteristics of the goods or service;`
  line
  line `(c) which consist exclusively of marks or indications which have become customary in the`
  line `current language or in the bona fide and established practices of the trade,`
  line `shall not be registered:`
  line
  line `Provided that a trade mark shall not be refused registration if before the date of application for`
  line `registration it has acquired a distinctive character as a result of the use made of it or is a well-known trade`
  line mark.
  line
  line `(2) A mark shall not be registered as a trade mark if--`
  line
  line `(a) it is of such nature as to deceive the public or cause confusion;`
  line
  line `(b) it contains or comprises of any matter likely to hurt the religious susceptibilities of any class`
  line `or section of the citizens of India;`
  line
  line `(c) it comprises or contains scandalous or obscene matter;`
  line
  line `(d) its use is prohibited under the Emblems and Names (Prevention of Improper Use) Act, 1950`
  line `(12 of 1950).`
  line
  line `(3) A mark shall not be registered as a trade mark if it consists exclusively of--`
  line
  line `(a) the shape of goods which results from the nature of the goods themselves; or`
  line
  line `(b) the shape of goods which is necessary to obtain a technical result; or`
  line
  line `(c) the shape which gives substantial value to the goods.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the nature of goods or services in relation to which`
  line `the trade mark is used or proposed to be used shall not be a ground for refusal of registration.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (16795)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Limitation as to colour.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16795&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) A trade mark may be limited wholly or in part to any combination`
  line `of colours and any such limitation shall be taken into consideration by the ^1[Registrae or the High Court, as the case may be,] having to decide on the`
  line `distinctive character of the trade mark.`
  line
  line `(2) So far as a trade mark is registered without limitation of colour, it shall be deemed to be registered`
  line `for all colours.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 21, for “tribunal” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line .
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (16796)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Relative grounds for refusal of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 40 of 2010, s. 2, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 8-7-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16796&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as provided in section 12, a trade mark`
  line `shall not be registered if, because of--`
  line
  line `(a) its identity with an earlier trade mark and similarity of goods or services covered by the trade`
  line `mark; or`
  line
  line `(b) its similarity to an earlier trade mark and the identity or similarity of the goods or services`
  line `covered by the trade mark,`
  line `there exists a likelihood of confusion on the part of the public, which includes the likelihood of`
  line `association with the earlier trade mark.`
  line
  line `(2) A trade mark which--`
  line
  line `(a) is identical with or similar to an earlier trade mark; and`
  line
  line `(b) is to be registered for goods or services which are not similar to those for which the earlier`
  line `trade mark is registered in the name of a different proprietor,`
  line `shall not be registered if or to the extent the earlier trade mark is a well-known trade mark in India and the`
  line `use of the later mark without due cause would take unfair advantage of or be detrimental to the distinctive`
  line `character or repute of the earlier trade mark.`
  line
  line `(3) A trade mark shall not be registered if, or to the extent that, its use in India is liable to be`
  line prevented--
  line
  line `(a) by virtue of any law in particular the law of passing off protecting an unregistered trade mark`
  line `used in the course of trade; or`
  line
  line `(b) by virtue of law of copyright.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in this section shall prevent the registration of a trade mark where the proprietor of the`
  line `earlier trade mark or other earlier right consents to the registration, and in such case the Registrar may`
  line `register the mark under special circumstances under section 12.`
  line
  line `Explanation.For the purposes of this section, earlier trade mark means--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) a registered trade mark or an application under section 18 bearing an earlier date of filing or`
  line `an international registration referred to in section 36E or convention application referred to in`
  line `section 154 which has a date of application earlier than that of the trade mark in question, taking`
  line `account, where appropriate, of the priorities claimed in respect of the trade marks;]`
  line
  line `(b) a trade mark which, on the date of the application for registration of the trade mark in`
  line `question, or where appropriate, of the priority claimed in respect of the application, was entitled to`
  line `protection as a well-known trade mark.`
  line
  line `(5) A trade mark shall not be refused registration on the grounds specified in sub-sections (2) and (3),`
  line `unless objection on any one or more of those grounds is raised in opposition proceedings by the proprietor`
  line `of the earlier trade mark.`
  line
  line `(6) The Registrar shall, while determining whether a trade mark is a well-known trade mark, take into`
  line `account any fact which he considers relevant for determining a trade mark as a well-known trade mark`
  line including--
  line
  line `(i) the knowledge or recognition of that trade mark in the relevant section of the public including`
  line `knowledge in India obtained as a result of promotion of the trade mark;`
  line
  line `(ii) the duration, extent and geographical area of any use of that trade mark;`
  line
  line `(iii) the duration, extent and geographical area of any promotion of the trade mark, including`
  line `advertising or publicity and presentation, at fairs or exhibition of the goods or services to which the`
  line `trade mark applies;`
  line
  line `(iv) the duration and geographical area of any registration of or any application for registration of`
  line `that trade mark under this Act to the extent that they reflect the use or recognition of the trade mark;`
  line
  line `(v) the record of successful enforcement of the rights in that trade mark, in particular the extent to`
  line `which the trade mark has been recognised as a well-known trade mark by any court or Registrar under`
  line `that record.`
  line
  line `(7) The Registrar shall, while determining as to whether a trade mark is known or recognised in a`
  line `relevant section of the public for the purposes of sub-section (6), take into account--`
  line
  line `(i) the number of actual or potential consumers of the goods or services;`
  line
  line `(ii) the number of persons involved in the channels of distribution of the goods or services;`
  line
  line `(iii) the business circles dealing with the goods or services,`
  line `to which that trade mark applies.`
  line
  line `(8) Where a trade mark has been determined to be well known in at least one relevant section of the`
  line `public in India by any court or Registrar, the Registrar shall consider that trade mark as a well-known`
  line `trade mark for registration under this Act.`
  line
  line `(9) The Registrar shall not require as a condition, for determining whether a trade mark is a`
  line `well-known trade mark, any of the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) that the trade mark has been used in India;`
  line
  line `(ii) that the trade mark has been registered;`
  line
  line `(iii) that the application for registration of the trade mark has been filed in India;`
  line
  line `(iv) that the trade mark--`
  line
  line `(a) is well-known in; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been registered in; or`
  line
  line `(c) in respect of which an application for registration has been filed in,`
  line `any jurisdiction other than India, or`
  line
  line `(v) that the trade mark is well-known to the public at large in India.`
  line
  line `(10) While considering an application for registration of a trade mark and opposition filed in respect`
  line `thereof, the Registrar shall--`
  line
  line `(i) protect a well-known trade mark against the identical or similar trade marks;`
  line
  line `(ii) take into consideration the bad faith involved either of the applicant or the opponent affecting`
  line `the right relating to the trade mark.`
  line
  line `(11) Where a trade mark has been registered in good faith disclosing the material informations to the`
  line `Registrar or where right to a trade mark has been acquired through use in good faith before the`
  line `commencement of this Act, then, nothing in this Act shall prejudice the validity of the registration of that`
  line `trade mark or right to use that trade mark on the ground that such trade mark is identical with or similar to`
  line `a well-known trade mark.`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (16797)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Registration in the case of honest concurrent use, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16797&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `In the case of honest concurrent use or`
  line `of other special circumstances which in the opinion of the Registrar, make it proper so to do, he may`
  line `permit the registration by more than one proprietor of the trade marks which are identical or similar`
  line `(whether any such trade mark is already registered or not) in respect of the same or similar goods or`
  line `services, subject to such conditions and limitations, if any, as the Registrar may think fit to impose.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (16798)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Prohibition of registration of names of chemical elements or international non-proprietary names.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16798&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `No word--`
  line
  line `(a) which is the commonly used and accepted name of any single chemical element or any single`
  line `chemical compound (as distinguished from a mixture) in respect of a chemical substance or`
  line `preparation, or`
  line
  line `(b) which is declared by the World Health Organisation and notified in the prescribed manner by`
  line `the Registrar from time to time, as an international non-proprietary name or which is deceptively`
  line `similar to such name,`
  line `shall be registered as a trade mark and any such registration shall be deemed for the purpose of section 57`
  line `to be an entry made in the register without sufficient cause or an entry wrongly remaining on the register,`
  line `as the circumstances may require.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (16799)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Use of names and representations of living persons or persons recently dead.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16799&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Where an`
  line `application is made for the registration of a trade mark which falsely suggests a connection with any`
  line `living person, or a person whose death took place within twenty years prior to the date of application for`
  line `registration of the trade mark, the Registrar may, before he proceeds with the application, require the`
  line `applicant to furnish him with the consent in writing of such living person or, as the case may be, of the`
  line `legal representative of the deceased person to the connection appearing on the trade mark, and may refuse`
  line `to proceed with the application unless the applicant furnishes the Registrar with such consent.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (16800)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Registration of parts of trade marks and of trade marks as a series.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16800&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the`
  line `proprietor of a trade mark claims to be entitled to the exclusive use of any part thereof separately, he may`
  line `apply to register the whole and the part as separate trade marks.`
  line
  line `(2) Each such separate trade mark shall satisfy all the conditions applying to and have all the incidents`
  line `of, an independent trade mark.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a person claiming to be the proprietor of several trade marks in respect of the same or`
  line `similar goods or services or description of goods or description of services, which, while resembling each`
  line `other in the material particulars thereof, yet differ in respect of--`
  line
  line `(a) statement of the goods or services in relation to which they are respectively used or proposed`
  line `to be used; or`
  line
  line `(b) statement of number, price, quality or names of places; or`
  line
  line `(c) other matter of a non-distinctive character which does not substantially affect the identity of`
  line `the trade mark; or`
  line
  line `(d) colour,`
  line `seeks to register those trade marks, they may be registered as a series in one registration.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (16801)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Registration of trade marks as associated trade marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16801&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a trade mark which is`
  line `registered, or is the subject of an application for registration, in respect of any goods or services is`
  line `identical with another trade mark which is registered, or is the subject of an application for registration, in`
  line `the name of the same proprietor in respect of the same goods or description of goods or same services or`
  line `description of services or so nearly resembles it as to be likely to deceive or cause confusion if used by a`
  line `person other than the proprietor, the Registrar may, at any time, require that the trade marks shall be`
  line `entered on the register as associated trade marks.`
  line
  line `(2) Where there is an identity or near resemblance of marks that are registered, or are the subject of`
  line `applications for registration in the name of the same proprietor, in respect of goods and services which are`
  line `associated with those goods or services, or goods or services of that description, sub-section (1) shall`
  line `apply as it applies as where there is an identity or near resemblance of marks that are registered, or are the`
  line `subject of applications for registration, in the name of the same proprietor in respect of the same goods or`
  line `description of goods or same services or description of services.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a trade mark and any part thereof are, in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 15, registered as separate trade marks in the name of the same proprietor, they shall be deemed`
  line `to be, and shall be registered as, associated trade marks.`
  line
  line `(4) All trade marks registered in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (3) of section 15 as a`
  line `series in one registration shall be deemed to be, and shall be registered as, associated trade marks.`
  line
  line `(5) On application made in the prescribed manner by the registered proprietor of two or more trade`
  line `marks registered as associated trade marks, the Registrar may dissolve the association as respects any of`
  line `them if he is satisfied that there would be no likelihood of deception or confusion being caused if that`
  line `trade mark were used by any other person in relation to any of the goods or services or both in respect of`
  line `which it is registered, and may amend the register accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (16802)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Effect of registration of parts of a mark.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16802&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a trade mark consists of several matters,`
  line `its registration shall confer on the proprietor exclusive right to the use of the trade mark taken as a whole.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), when a trade mark--`
  line
  line `(a) contains any part--`
  line
  line `(i) which is not the subject of a separate application by the proprietor for registration as a`
  line `trade mark; or`
  line
  line `(ii) which is not separately registered by the proprietor as a trade mark; or`
  line
  line `(b) contains any matter which is common to the trade or is otherwise of a non-distinctive`
  line character,
  line `the registration thereof shall not confer any exclusive right in the matter forming only a part of the whole`
  line `of the trade mark so registered.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (16803)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Application for registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16803&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person claiming to be the proprietor of a trade mark used`
  line `or proposed to be used by him, who is desirous of registering it, shall apply in writing to the Registrar in`
  line `the prescribed manner for the registration of his trade mark.`
  line
  line `(2) A single application may be made for registration of a trade mark for different classes of goods`
  line `and services and fee payable therefor shall be in respect of each such class of goods or services.`
  line
  line `(3) Every application under sub-section (1) shall be filed in the office of the Trade Marks Registry`
  line `within whose territorial limits the principal place of business in India of the applicant or in the case of`
  line `joint applicants the principal place of business in India of the applicant whose name is first mentioned in`
  line `the application as having a place of business in India, is situate:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the applicant or any of the joint applicants does not carry on business in India,`
  line `the application shall be filed in the office of the Trade Marks Registry within whose territorial limits the`
  line `place mentioned in the address for service in India as disclosed in the application, is situate.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Registrar may refuse the application or may accept it`
  line `absolutely or subject to such amendments, modifications, conditions or limitations, if any, as he may`
  line `think fit.`
  line
  line `(5) In the case of a refusal or conditional acceptance of an application, the Registrar shall record in`
  line `writing the grounds for such refusal or conditional acceptance and the materials used by him in arriving at`
  line `his decision.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (16804)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Withdrawal of acceptance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16804&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Where, after the acceptance of an application for registration of a`
  line `trade mark but before its registration, the Registrar is satisfied--`
  line
  line `(a) that the application has been accepted in error; or`
  line
  line `(b) that in the circumstances of the case the trade mark should not be registered or should be`
  line `registered subject to conditions or limitations or to conditions additional to or different from the`
  line `conditions or limitations subject to which the application has been accepted,`
  line `the Registrar may, after hearing the applicant if he so desires, withdraw the acceptance and proceed as if`
  line `the application had not been accepted.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (16805)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Advertisement of application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16805&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) When an application for registration of a trade mark has`
  line `been accepted, whether absolutely or subject to conditions or limitations, the Registrar shall, as soon as`
  line `may be after acceptance, cause the application as accepted together with the conditions or limitations, if`
  line `any, subject to which it has been accepted, to be advertised in the prescribed manner:`
  line `Provided that the Registrar may cause the application to be advertised before acceptance if it relates`
  line `to a trade mark to which sub-section (1) of section 9 and sub-sections (1) and (2) of section 11 apply, or in`
  line `any other case where it appears to him that it is expedient by reason of any exceptional circumstances so`
  line `to do.`
  line
  line `(2) Where--`
  line
  line `(a) an application has been advertised before acceptance under sub-section (1); or`
  line
  line `(b) after advertisement of an application,--`
  line
  line `(i) an error in the application has been corrected; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the application has been permitted to be amended under section 22,`
  line `the Registrar may in his discretion cause the application to be advertised again or in any case falling under`
  line `clause (b) may, instead of causing the application to be advertised again, notify in the prescribed manner`
  line `the correction or amendment made in the application.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (16806)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Opposition to registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1 1. Subs. by Act 40 of 2010, s. 3, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 8-7-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16806&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `^1 [(1) Any person may, within four months from the date of the`
  line `advertisement or re-advertisement of an application for registration, give notice in writing in the`
  line `prescribed manner and on payment of such fee as may be prescribed, to the Registrar, of opposition to the`
  line registration.]
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar shall serve a copy of the notice on the applicant for registration and, within two`
  line `months from the receipt by the applicant of such copy of the notice of opposition, the applicant shall send`
  line `to the Registrar in the prescribed manner a counterstatement of the grounds on which he relies for his`
  line `application, and if he does not do so he shall be deemed to have abandoned his application.`
  line
  line `(3) If the applicant sends such counter-statement, the Registrar shall serve a copy thereof on the`
  line `person giving notice of opposition.`
  line
  line `(4) Any evidence upon which the opponent and the applicant may rely shall be submitted in the`
  line `prescribed manner and within the prescribed time to the Registrar, and the Registrar shall give an`
  line `opportunity to them to be heard, if they so desire.`
  line
  line `(5) The Registrar shall, after hearing the parties, if so required, and considering the evidence, decide`
  line `whether and subject to what conditions or limitations, if any, the registration is to be permitted, and may`
  line `take into account a ground of objection whether relied upon by the opponent or not.`
  line
  line `(6) Where a person giving notice of opposition or an applicant sending a counter-statement after`
  line `receipt of a copy of such notice neither resides nor carries on business in India, the Registrar may require`
  line `him to give security for the costs of proceedings before him, and in default of such security being duly`
  line `given, may treat the opposition or application, as the case may be, as abandoned.`
  line
  line `(7) The Registrar may, on request, permit correction of any error in, or any amendment of, a notice of`
  line `opposition or a counter-statement on such terms as he thinks just.`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (16807)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Correction and amendment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16807&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The Registrar may, on such terms as he thinks just, at any time,`
  line `whether before or after acceptance of an application for registration under section 18, permit the`
  line `correction of any error in or in connection with the application or permit an amendment of the`
  line `application:`
  line
  line `Provided that if an amendment is made to a single application referred to in sub-section (2) of section`
  line `18 involving division of such application into two or more applications, the date of making of the initial`
  line `application shall be deemed to be the date of making of the divided applications so divided.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (16808)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title Registration.
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 8-7-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16808&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of section 19, when an application for registration of`
  line `a trade mark has been accepted and either--`
  line
  line `(a) the application has not been opposed and the time for notice of opposition has expired; or`
  line
  line `(b) the application has been opposed and the opposition has been decided in favour of the`
  line applicant,
  line `the Registrar shall, unless the Central Government otherwise directs, register the said trade mark ^1[within`
  line `eighteen months of the filing of the application] and the trade mark when registered shall be registered as`
  line `of the date of the making of the said application and that date shall, subject to the provisions of section`
  line `154, be deemed to be the date of registration.`
  line
  line `(2) On the registration of a trade mark, the Registrar shall issue to the applicant a certificate in the`
  line `prescribed form of the registration thereof, sealed with the seal of the Trade Marks Registry.`
  line
  line `(3) Where registration of a trade mark is not completed within twelve months from the date of the`
  line `application by reason of default on the part of the applicant, the Registrar may, after giving notice to the`
  line `applicant in the prescribed manner, treat the application as abandoned unless it is completed within the`
  line `time specified in that behalf in the notice.`
  line
  line `(4) The Registrar may amend the register or a certificate of registration for the purpose of correcting a`
  line `clerical error or an obvious mistake.`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (16809)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Jointly owned trade marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16809&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as provided in sub-section (2), nothing in this Act shall`
  line `authorise the registration of two or more persons who use a trade mark independently, or propose so as to`
  line `use it, as joint proprietors thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the relations between two or more persons interested in a trade mark are such that no one`
  line `of them is entitled as between himself and the other or others of them to use it except--`
  line
  line `(a) on behalf of both or all of them; or`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to an article or service with which both or all of them are connected in the course of`
  line trade,
  line `those persons may be registered as joint proprietors of the trade mark, and this Act shall have effect in`
  line `relation to any rights to the use of the trade mark vested in those persons as if those rights had been vested`
  line `in a single person.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (16810)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Duration, renewal, removal and restoration of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16810&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The registration of a trade`
  line `mark, after the commencement of this Act, shall be for a period of ten years, but may be renewed from`
  line `time to time in accordance with the provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar shall, on application made by the registered proprietor of a trade mark in the`
  line `prescribed manner and within the prescribed period and subject to payment of the prescribed fee, renew`
  line `the registration of the trade mark for a period of ten years from the date of expiration of the original`
  line `registration or of the last renewal of registration, as the case may be (which date is in this section referred`
  line `to as the expiration of the last registration).`
  line
  line `(3) At the prescribed time before the expiration of the last registration of a trade mark the Registrar`
  line `shall send notice in the prescribed manner to the registered proprietor of the date of expiration and the`
  line `conditions as to payment of fees and otherwise upon which a renewal of registration may be obtained,`
  line `and, if at the expiration of the time prescribed in that behalf those conditions have not been duly complied`
  line `with the Registrar may remove the trade mark from the register:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Registrar shall not remove the trade mark from the register if an application is made`
  line `in the prescribed form and the prescribed fee and surcharge is paid within six months from the expiration`
  line `of the last registration of the trade mark and shall renew the registration of the trade mark for a period of`
  line `ten years under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) Where a trade mark has been removed from the register for non-payment of the prescribed fee, the`
  line `Registrar shall, after six months and within one year from the expiration of the last registration of the`
  line `trade mark, on receipt of an application in the prescribed form and on payment of the prescribed fee, if`
  line `satisfied that it is just so to do, restore the trade mark to the register and renew the registration of the trade`
  line `mark either generally or subject to such conditions or limitations as he thinks fit to impose, for a period of`
  line `ten years from the expiration of the last registration.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (16811)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Effect of removal from register for failure to pay fee for renewal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes `1.Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 21, for “Tribunal” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16811&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Where a trade mark has`
  line `been removed from the register for failure to pay the fee for renewal, it shall nevertheless, for the purpose`
  line `of any application for the registration of another trade mark during one year, next after the date of the`
  line `removal, be deemed to be a trade mark already on the register, unless the ^1[Registrar or the High Court, as the case may be,] is satisfied either--`
  line
  line `(a) that there has been no bona fide trade use of the trade mark which has been removed during`
  line `the two years immediately preceding its removal; or`
  line
  line `(b) that no deception or confusion would be likely to arise from the use of the trade mark which is`
  line `the subject of the application for registration by reason of any previous use of the trade mark which`
  line `has been removed.`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (16812)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `No action for infringement of unregistered trade mark.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16812&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall be entitled to`
  line `institute any proceeding to prevent, or to recover damages for, the infringement of an unregistered trade`
  line mark.
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this Act shall be deemed to affect rights of action against any person for passing off`
  line `goods or services as the goods of another person or as services provided by another person, or the`
  line `remedies in respect thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (16813)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Rights conferred by registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16813&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, the`
  line `registration of a trade mark shall, if valid, give to the registered proprietor of the trade mark the exclusive`
  line `right to the use of the trade mark in relation to the goods or services in respect of which the trade mark is`
  line `registered and to obtain relief in respect of infringement of the trade mark in the manner provided by this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2) The exclusive right to the use of a trade mark given under sub-section (1) shall be subject to any`
  line `conditions and limitations to which the registration is subject.`
  line
  line `(3) Where two or more persons are registered proprietors of trade marks, which are identical with or`
  line `nearly resemble each other, the exclusive right to the use of any of those trade marks shall not (except so`
  line `far as their respective rights are subject to any conditions or limitations entered on the register) be deemed`
  line `to have been acquired by any one of those persons as against any other of those persons merely by`
  line `registration of the trade marks but each of those persons has otherwise the same rights as against other`
  line `persons (not being registered users using by way of permitted use) as he would have if he were the sole`
  line `registered proprietor.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (16814)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Infringement of registered trade marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16814&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) A registered trade mark is infringed by a person`
  line `who, not being a registered proprietor or a person using by way of permitted use, uses in the course of`
  line `trade, a mark which is identical with, or deceptively similar to, the trade mark in relation to goods or`
  line `services in respect of which the trade mark is registered and in such manner as to render the use of the`
  line `mark likely to be taken as being used as a trade mark.`
  line
  line `(2) A registered trade mark is infringed by a person who, not being a registered proprietor or a person`
  line `using by way of permitted use, uses in the course of trade, a mark which because of--`
  line
  line `(a) its identity with the registered trade mark and the similarity of the goods or services covered`
  line `by such registered trade mark; or`
  line
  line `(b) its similarity to the registered trade mark and the identity or similarity of the goods or services`
  line `covered by such registered trade mark; or`
  line
  line `(c) its identity with the registered trade mark and the identity of the goods or services covered by`
  line `such registered trade mark,`
  line `is likely to cause confusion on the part of the public, or which is likely to have an association with the`
  line `registered trade mark.`
  line
  line `(3) In any case falling under clause (c) of sub-section (2), the court shall presume that it is likely to`
  line `cause confusion on the part of the public.`
  line
  line `(4) A registered trade mark is infringed by a person who, not being a registered proprietor or a person`
  line `using by way of permitted use, uses in the course of trade, a mark which--`
  line
  line `(a) is identical with or similar to the registered trade mark; and`
  line
  line `(b) is used in relation to goods or services which are not similar to those for which the trade mark`
  line `is registered; and`
  line
  line `(c) the registered trade mark has a reputation in India and the use of the mark without due cause`
  line `takes unfair advantage of or is detrimental to, the distinctive character or repute of the registered trade`
  line mark.
  line
  line `(5) A registered trade mark is infringed by a person if he uses such registered trade mark, as his trade`
  line `name or part of his trade name, or name of his business concern or part of the name, of his business`
  line `concern dealing in goods or services in respect of which the trade mark is registered.`
  line
  line `(6) For the purposes of this section, a person uses a registered mark, if, in particular, he--`
  line
  line `(a) affixes it to goods or the packaging thereof;`
  line
  line `(b) offers or exposes goods for sale, puts them on the market, or stocks them for those purposes`
  line `under the registered trade mark, or offers or supplies services under the registered trade mark;`
  line
  line `(c) imports or exports goods under the mark; or`
  line
  line `(d) uses the registered trade mark on business papers or in advertising.`
  line
  line `(7) A registered trade mark is infringed by a person who applies such registered trade mark to a`
  line `material intended to be used for labeling or packaging goods, as a business paper, or for advertising goods`
  line `or services, provided such person, when he applied the mark, knew or had reason to believe that the`
  line `application of the mark was not duly authorised by the proprietor or a licensee.`
  line
  line `(8) A registered trade mark is infringed by any advertising of that trade mark if such advertising--`
  line
  line `(a) takes unfair advantage of and is contrary to honest practices in industrial or commercial`
  line `matters; or`
  line
  line `(b) is detrimental to its distinctive character; or`
  line
  line `(c) is against the reputation of the trade mark.`
  line
  line `(9) Where the distinctive elements of a registered trade mark consist of or include words, the trade`
  line `mark may be infringed by the spoken use of those words as well as by their visual representation and`
  line `reference in this section to the use of a mark shall be construed accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (16815)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Limits on effect of registered trade mark.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16815&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing in section 29 shall be construed as`
  line `preventing the use of a registered trade mark by any person for the purposes of identifying goods or`
  line `services as those of the proprietor provided the use--`
  line
  line `(a) is in accordance with honest practices in industrial or commercial matters, and`
  line
  line `(b) is not such as to take unfair advantage of or be detrimental to the distinctive character or`
  line `repute of the trade mark.`
  line
  line `(2) A registered trade mark is not infringed where--`
  line
  line `(a) the use in relation to goods or services indicates the kind, quality, quantity, intended purpose,`
  line `value, geographical origin, the time of production of goods or of rendering of services or other`
  line `characteristics of goods or services;`
  line
  line `(b) a trade mark is registered subject to any conditions or limitations, the use of the trade mark in`
  line `any manner in relation to goods to be sold or otherwise traded in, in any place, or in relation to goods`
  line `to be exported to any market or in relation to services for use or available for acceptance in any place`
  line `or country outside India or in any other circumstances, to which, having regard to those conditions or`
  line `limitations, the registration does not extend;`
  line
  line `(c) the use by a person of a trade mark--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to goods connected in the course of trade with the proprietor or a registered user`
  line `of the trade mark if, as to those goods or a bulk of which they form part, the registered proprietor`
  line `or the registered user conforming to the permitted use has applied the trade mark and has not`
  line `subsequently removed or obliterated it, or has at any time expressly or impliedly consented to the`
  line `use of the trade mark; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to services to which the proprietor of such mark or of a registered user`
  line `conforming to the permitted use has applied the mark, where the purpose and effect of the use of`
  line `the mark is to indicate, in accordance with the fact, that those services have been performed by`
  line `the proprietor or a registered user of the mark;`
  line
  line `(d) the use of a trade mark by a person in relation to goods adapted to form part of, or to be`
  line `accessory to, other goods or services in relation to which the trade mark has been used without`
  line `infringement of the right given by registration under this Act or might for the time being be so used, if`
  line `the use of the trade mark is reasonably necessary in order to indicate that the goods or services are so`
  line `adapted, and neither the purpose nor the effect of the use of the trade mark is to indicate, otherwise than in accordance with the fact, a connection in the course of trade between any person and the`
  line `goods or services, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(e) the use of a registered trade mark, being one of two or more trade marks registered under this`
  line `Act which are identical or nearly resemble each other, in exercise of the right to the use of that trade`
  line `mark given by registration under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the goods bearing a registered trade mark are lawfully acquired by a person, the sale of the`
  line `goods in the market or otherwise dealing in those goods by that person or by a person claiming under or`
  line `through him is not infringement of a trade mark by reason only of--`
  line
  line `(a) the registered trade mark having been assigned by the registered proprietor to some other`
  line `person, after the acquisition of those goods; or`
  line
  line `(b) the goods having been put on the market under the registered trade mark by the proprietor or`
  line `with his consent.`
  line
  line `(4) Sub-section (3) shall not apply where there exists legitimate reasons for the proprietor to oppose`
  line `further dealings in the goods in particular, where the condition of the goods, has been changed or`
  line `impaired after they have been put on the market.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (16816)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Registration to be prima facie evidence of validity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16816&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) In all legal proceedings relating to a`
  line `trade mark registered under this Act (including applications under section 57), the original registration of`
  line `the trade mark and of all subsequent assignments and transmissions of the trade mark shall be prima facie`
  line `evidence of the validity thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) In all legal proceedings as aforesaid a registered trade mark shall not be held to be invalid on the`
  line `ground that it was not a registrable trade mark under section 9 except upon evidence of distinctiveness`
  line `and that such evidence was not submitted to the Registrar before registration, if it is proved that the trade`
  line `mark had been so used by the registered proprietor or his predecessor in title as to have become`
  line `distinctive at the date of registration.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (16817)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Protection of registration on ground of distinctiveness in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16817&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Where a trade mark`
  line `is registered in breach of sub-section (1) of section 9, it shall not be declared invalid if, in consequence of`
  line `the use which has been made of it, it has after registration and before commencement of any legal`
  line `proceedings challenging the validity of such registration, acquired a distinctive character in relation to the`
  line `goods or services for which it is registered.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (16818)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Effect of acquiescence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16818&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the proprietor of an earlier trade mark has acquiesced for a`
  line `continuous period of five years in the use of a registered trade mark, being aware of that use, he shall no`
  line `longer be entitled on the basis of that earlier trade mark--`
  line
  line `(a) to apply for a declaration that the registration of the later trade mark is invalid, or`
  line
  line `(b) to oppose the use of the later trade mark in relation to the goods or services in relation to`
  line `which it has been so used,`
  line `unless the registration of the later trade mark was not applied in good faith.`
  line
  line `(2) Where sub-section (1) applies, the proprietor of the later trade mark is not entitled to oppose the`
  line `use of the earlier trade mark, or as the case may be, the exploitation of the earlier right, notwithstanding`
  line `that the earlier trade mark may no longer be invoked against his later trade mark.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (16819)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Saving for vested rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16819&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall entitle the proprietor or a registered user of`
  line `registered trade mark to interfere with or restrain the use by any person of a trade mark identical with or`
  line `nearly resembling it in relation to goods or services in relation to which that person or a predecessor in`
  line `title of his has continuously used that trade mark from a date prior--`
  line
  line `(a) to the use of the first-mentioned trade mark in relation to those goods or services by the`
  line `proprietor or a predecessor in title of his; or`
  line
  line `(b) to the date of registration of the first-mentioned trade mark in respect of those goods or`
  line `services in the name of the proprietor of a predecessor in title of his;`
  line
  line `whichever is the earlier, and the Registrar shall not refuse (on such use being proved) to register the`
  line `second mentioned trade mark by reason only of the registration of the first-mentioned trade mark.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (16820)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Saving for use of name, address or description of goods or services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16820&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act`
  line `shall entitle the proprietor or a registered user of a registered trade mark to interfere with any bona fide`
  line `use by a person of his own name or that of his place of business, or of the name, or of the name of the`
  line `place of business, of any of his predecessors in business, or the use by any person of any bona fide`
  line `description of the character or quality of his goods or services.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (16821)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Saving for words used as name or description of an article or substance or service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16821&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `registration of a trade mark shall not be deemed to have become invalid by reason only of any use after`
  line `the date of the registration of any word or words which the trade mark contains or of which it consists as`
  line `the name or description of an article or substance or service:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if it is proved either--`
  line
  line `(a) that there is a well known and established use of the said word as the name or description of`
  line `the article or substance or service by a person or persons carrying on trade therein, not being use in`
  line `relation to goods or services connected in the course of trade with the proprietor or a registered user`
  line `of the trade mark or (in the case of a certification trade mark) in relation to goods or services certified`
  line `by the proprietor; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the article or substance was formerly manufactured under a patent that a period of two`
  line `years or more after the cesser of the patent has elapsed and that the said word is the only practicable`
  line `name or description of the article or substance,`
  line `the provisions of sub-section (2) shall apply.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the facts mentioned in clause (a) or clause (b) of the proviso to sub-section (1) are proved`
  line `with respect to any words, then,--`
  line
  line `(a) for the purposes of any proceedings under section 57 if the trade mark consists solely of such`
  line `words, the registration of the trade mark, so far as regards registration in respect of the article or`
  line `substance in question or of any goods of the same description, or of the services or of any services of`
  line `the same description, as the case requires, shall be deemed to be an entry wrongly remaining on the`
  line register;
  line
  line `(b) for the purposes of any other legal proceedings relating to the trade mark,--`
  line
  line `(i) if the trade mark consists solely of such words, all rights of the proprietor under this Act or`
  line `any other law to the use of the trade mark; or`
  line
  line `(ii) if the trade mark contains such words and other matter, all such right of the proprietor to`
  line `the use of such words,`
  line `in relation to the article or substance or to any goods of the same description, or to the service or to any`
  line `services of the same description, as the case requires, shall be deemed to have ceased on the date on`
  line `which the use mentioned in clause (a) of the proviso to sub-section (1) first became well known and`
  line `established or at the expiration of the period of two years mentioned in clause (b) of the said proviso.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36_a:
  sectionId (16822)
  sectionNo 36A
  orderNo 37
  title `Application of Act in case of international registration under Madrid Protocol.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 40 of 2010, s. 5 (w.e.f. 8-7-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16822&sectionno=36A&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_36_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[36A. Application of Act in case of international registration under Madrid Protocol.--The`
  line `provisions of this Chapter shall apply to international applications and international registrations under`
  line `the Madrid Protocol.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_b:
  sectionId (16823)
  sectionNo 36B
  orderNo 38
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 2010, s. 5 (w.e.f. 8-7-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16823&sectionno=36B&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_36_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[36B. Definitions.--In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "application", in relation to a Contracting State or a Contracting Organisation, means an`
  line `application made by a person who is a citizen of, or is domiciled in, or has a real and effective industrial or commercial establishment in, that Contracting State or a State which is a member of that`
  line `Contracting Organisation, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause, "real and effective industrial or commercial`
  line `establishment" means and includes any establishment where some bona fide industrial or commercial`
  line `activity takes place and need not necessarily be the principal place of business;`
  line
  line `(b) "basic application" means an application for the registration of a trade mark filed under`
  line `section 18 and which is used as a basis for applying for an international registration;`
  line
  line `(c) "basic registration" means the registration of a trade mark under section 23 and which is used`
  line `as a basis for applying for an international registration;`
  line
  line `(d) "Common Regulations" means the Regulations concerning the implementation of the Madrid`
  line Protocol;
  line
  line `(e) "Contracting Organisation" means a Contracting Party that is an intergovernmental`
  line organisation;
  line
  line `(f) "Contracting Party" means a Contracting State or Contracting Organisation party to the`
  line `Madrid Protocol;`
  line
  line `(g) "Contracting State" means a country party to the Madrid Protocol;`
  line
  line `(h) "international application" means an application for international registration or for extension`
  line `of the protection resulting from an international registration to any Contracting Party made under the`
  line `Madrid Protocol;`
  line
  line `(i) "International Bureau" means the International Bureau of the World Intellectual Property`
  line Organisation;
  line
  line `(j) "international registration" means the registration of a trade mark in the register of the`
  line `International Bureau effected under the Madrid Protocol;`
  line
  line `(k) "Madrid Agreement" means the Madrid Agreement Concerning the International Registration`
  line `of Marks adopted at Madrid on the 14th day of April, 1891, as subsequently revised and amended;`
  line
  line `(l) "Madrid Protocol" means the Protocol relating to the Madrid Agreement Concerning the`
  line `International Registration of Marks adopted at Madrid on the 27th day of June, 1989, as amended`
  line `from time to time.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_c:
  sectionId (16824)
  sectionNo 36C
  orderNo 39
  title `Trade Marks Registry to deal with international applications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 2010, s. 5 (w.e.f. 8-7-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16824&sectionno=36C&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_36_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[36C. Trade Marks Registry to deal with international applications.--Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in sub-section (3) of section 5, an international application shall be dealt with by the head office`
  line `of the Trade Marks Registry or such branch office of the Registry, as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_d:
  sectionId (16825)
  sectionNo 36D
  orderNo 40
  title `International application originating from India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 2010, s. 5 (w.e.f. 8-7-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16825&sectionno=36D&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_36_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[36D. International application originating from India.--(1) Where an application for the`
  line `registration of a trade mark has been made under section 18 or a trade mark has been registered under`
  line `section 23, the applicant or the registered proprietor may make an international application on the form`
  line `prescribed by the Common Regulations for international registration of that trade mark.`
  line
  line `(2) A person holding an international registration may make an international application on the form`
  line `prescribed by the Common Regulations for extension of the protection resulting from such registration to`
  line `any other Contracting Party.`
  line
  line `(3) An international application under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall designate the`
  line `Contracting Parties where the protection resulting from the international registration is required.`
  line
  line `(4) The Registrar shall certify in the prescribed manner that the particulars appearing in the`
  line `international application correspond to the particulars appearing, at the time of the certification, in the`
  line `application under section 18 or the registration under section 23, and shall indicate the date and number of`
  line `that application or the date and number of that registration as well as the date and number of the`
  line `application from which that registration resulted, as the case may be, and shall within the prescribed`
  line `period, forward the international application to the International Bureau for registration, also indicating`
  line `the date of the international application.`
  line
  line `(5) Where at any time before the expiry of a period of five years of an international registration,`
  line `whether such registration has been transferred to another person or not, the application under section 18`
  line `or the registration under section 23, as the case may be, has been withdrawn or cancelled or has expired or`
  line `has been finally refused in respect of all or some of the goods or services listed in the international`
  line `registration, the protection resulting from such international registration shall cease to have effect:`
  line
  line `Provided that where an appeal is made against the decision of registration and an action requesting for`
  line `withdrawal of application or an opposition to the application has been initiated before the expiry of the`
  line `period of five years of an international registration, any final decision resulting into withdrawal,`
  line `cancellation, expiration or refusal shall be deemed to have taken place before the expiry of five years of`
  line `the international registration.`
  line
  line `(6) The Registrar shall, during the period of five years beginning with the date of international`
  line `registration, transmit to the International Bureau every information referred to in sub-section (5).`
  line
  line `(7) The Registrar shall notify the International Bureau the cancellation to be effected to an`
  line `international registration keeping in view the current status of the basic application or the basic`
  line `registration, as the case may be.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_e:
  sectionId (16826)
  sectionNo 36E
  orderNo 41
  title `International registrations where India has been designated.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 2010, s. 5 (w.e.f. 8-7-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16826&sectionno=36E&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_36_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[36E. International registrations where India has been designated.--(1) The Registrar shall, after`
  line `receipt of an advice from the International Bureau about any international registration where India has`
  line `been designated, keep a record of the particulars of that international registration in the prescribed`
  line manner.
  line
  line `(2) Where, after recording the particulars of any international registration referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1), the Registrar is satisfied that in the circumstances of the case the protection of trade mark`
  line `in India should not be granted or such protection should be granted subject to conditions or limitations or`
  line `to conditions additional to or different from the conditions or limitations subject to which the international`
  line `registration has been accepted, he may, after hearing the applicant if he so desires, refuse grant of`
  line `protection and inform the International Bureau in the prescribed manner within eighteen months from the`
  line `date on which the advice referred to in sub-section (1) was received.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Registrar finds nothing in the particulars of an international registration to refuse grant`
  line `of protection under sub-section (2), he shall within the prescribed period cause such international`
  line `registration to be advertised in the prescribed manner.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of sections 9 to 21 (both inclusive), 63 and 74 shall apply mutatis mutandis in`
  line `relation to an international registration as if such international registration was an application for`
  line `registration of a trade mark under section 18.`
  line
  line `(5) When the protection of an international registration has not been opposed and the time for notice`
  line `of opposition has expired, the Registrar shall within a period of eighteen months of the receipt of advice`
  line `under sub-section (1) notify the International Bureau its acceptance of extension of protection of the trade`
  line `mark under such international registration and, in case the Registrar fails to notify the International`
  line `Bureau, it shall be deemed that the protection has been extended to the trade mark.`
  line
  line `(6) Where a registered proprietor of a trade mark makes an international registration of that trade`
  line `mark and designates India, the international registration from the date of the registration shall be deemed`
  line `to replace the registration held in India without prejudice to any right acquired under such previously held`
  line `registration and the Registrar shall, upon request by the applicant, make necessary entry in the register`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1) of section 6.`
  line
  line `(7) A holder of international registration of a trade mark who designates India and who has not been`
  line `extended protection in India shall have the same remedy which is available to any person making an`
  line `application for the registration of a trade mark under section 18 and which has not resulted in registration`
  line `under section 23.`
  line
  line `(8) Where at any time before the expiry of a period of five years of an international registration,`
  line `whether such registration has been transferred to another person or not, the related basic application or, as`
  line `the case may be, the basic registration in a Contracting Party other than India has been withdrawn or`
  line `cancelled or has expired or has been finally refused in respect of all or some of the goods or services listed in the international registration, the protection resulting from such international registration in India`
  line `shall cease to have effect.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_f:
  sectionId (16827)
  sectionNo 36F
  orderNo 42
  title `Effects of international registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_f_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 2010, s. 5 (w.e.f. 8-7-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16827&sectionno=36F&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_36_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[36F. Effects of international registration.--(1) From the date of the international registration of a`
  line `trade mark where India has been designated or the date of the recording in the register of the International`
  line `Bureau about the extension of the protection resulting from an international registration of a trade mark to`
  line `India, the protection of the trade mark in India shall be the same as if the trade mark had been registered`
  line `in India.`
  line
  line `(2) The indication of classes of goods and services given by the applicant shall not bind the Registrar`
  line `with regard to the determination of the scope of the protection of the trade mark.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_g:
  sectionId (16828)
  sectionNo 36G
  orderNo 43
  title `Duration and renewal of international registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_g_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 2010, s. 5 (w.e.f. 8-7-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16828&sectionno=36G&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_36_g_content:
  string
  line `^1[36G. Duration and renewal of international registration.--(1) The international registration of a`
  line `trade mark at the International Bureau shall be for a period of ten years and may be renewed for a period`
  line `of ten years from the expiry of the preceding period.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to payment of a surcharge prescribed by the rules, a grace period of six months shall be`
  line `allowed for renewal of the international registration.]`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (16829)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 44
  title `Power of registered proprietor to assign and give receipts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16829&sectionno=37&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `The person for the time being`
  line `entered in the register as proprietor of a trade mark shall, subject to the provisions of this Act and to any`
  line `rights appearing from the register to be vested in any other person, have power to assign the trade mark,`
  line `and to give effectual receipts for any consideration for such assignment.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (16830)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 45
  title `Assignability and transmissibility of registered trade marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16830&sectionno=38&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in`
  line `any other law to the contrary, a registered trade mark shall, subject to the provisions of this Chapter, be`
  line `assignable and transmissible, whether with or without the goodwill of the business concerned and in`
  line `respect either of all the goods or services in respect of which the trade mark is registered or of some only`
  line `of those goods or services.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (16831)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 46
  title `Assignability and transmissibility of unregistered trade marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16831&sectionno=39&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `An unregistered trade mark`
  line `may be assigned or transmitted with or without the goodwill of the business concerned.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (16832)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 47
  title `Restriction on assignment or transmission where multiple exclusive rights would be created.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16832&sectionno=40&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything in sections 38 and 39, a trade mark shall not be assignable or`
  line `transmissible in a case in which as a result of the assignment or transmission there would in the`
  line `circumstances subsist, whether under this Act or any other law, exclusive rights in more than one of the`
  line `persons concerned to the use, in relation to--`
  line
  line `(a) same goods or services;`
  line
  line `(b) same description of goods or services;`
  line
  line `(c) goods or services or description of goods or services which are associated with each other,`
  line
  line `of trade marks nearly resembling each other or of identical trade mark, if having regard to the similarity`
  line `of the goods and services and to the similarity of the trade marks, the use of the trade marks in exercise of`
  line `those rights would be likely to deceive or cause confusion:`
  line
  line `Provided that an assignment or transmission shall not be deemed to be invalid under this sub-section`
  line `if the exclusive rights subsisting as a result thereof in the persons concerned respectively are, having`
  line `regard to limitations imposed thereon, such as not to be exercisable by two or more of those persons in`
  line `relation to goods to be sold, or otherwise traded in, within India otherwise than for export therefrom, or in`
  line `relation to goods to be exported to the same market outside India or in relation to services for use at any`
  line `place in India or any place outside India in relation to services available for acceptance in India.`
  line
  line `(2) The proprietor of a registered trade mark who proposes to assign it may submit to the Registrar in`
  line `the prescribed manner a statement of case setting out the circumstances and the Registrar may issue to`
  line `him a certificate stating whether, having regard to the similarity of the goods or services and of the trade`
  line `marks referred to in the case, the proposed assignment would or would not be invalid under sub-section (1), and a certificate so issued shall, subject to appeal and unless it is shown that the`
  line `certificate was obtained by fraud or misrepresentation, be conclusive as to the validity or invalidity under`
  line `sub-section (1) of the assignment in so far as such validity or invalidity depends upon the facts set out in`
  line `the case, but, as regards a certificate in favour of validity, only if application for the registration under`
  line `section 45 of the title of the person becoming entitled is made within six months from the date on which`
  line `the certificate is issued.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (16833)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 48
  title `Restriction on assignment or transmission when exclusive rights would be created in different parts of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16833&sectionno=41&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in sections 38 and 39, a trade mark shall not be`
  line `assignable or transmissible in a case in which as a result of the assignment or transmission there would in`
  line `the circumstances subsist, whether under this Act or any other law--`
  line
  line `(a) an exclusive right in one of the persons concerned, to the use of the trade mark limited to use`
  line `in relation to goods to be sold or otherwise traded in, in any place in India, or in relation to services`
  line `for use, or services available for acceptance in any place in India; and`
  line
  line `(b) an exclusive right in another of these persons concerned, to the use of a trade mark nearly`
  line `resembling the first-mentioned trade mark or of an identical trade mark in relation to--`
  line
  line `(i) the same goods or services; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the same description of goods or services; or`
  line
  line `(iii) services which are associated with those goods or goods of that description or goods`
  line `which are associated with those services or services of that description,`
  line
  line `limited to use in relation to goods to be sold or otherwise traded in, or services for use, or available for`
  line `acceptance, in any other place in India:`
  line
  line `Provided that in any such case, on application in the prescribed manner by the proprietor of a trade`
  line `mark who proposes to assign it, or by a person who claims that a registered trade mark has been`
  line `transmitted to him or to a predecessor in title of his since the commencement of this Act, the Registrar, if`
  line `he is satisfied that in all the circumstances the use of the trade mark in exercise of the said rights would`
  line `not be contrary to the public interest may approve the assignment or transmission, and an assignment or`
  line `transmission so approved shall not, unless it is shown that the approval was obtained by fraud or`
  line `misrepresentation, be deemed to be invalid under this section or section 40 if application for the`
  line `registration under section 45 of the title of the person becoming entitled is made within six months from`
  line `the date on which the approval is given or, in the case of a transmission, was made before that date.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (16834)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 49
  title `Conditions for assignment otherwise than in connection with the goodwill of a business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16834&sectionno=42&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `Where an assignment of a trade mark, whether registered or unregistered is made otherwise than in`
  line `connection with the goodwill of the business in which the mark has been or is used, the assignment shall`
  line `not take effect unless the assignee, not later than the expiration of six months from the date on which the`
  line `assignment is made or within such extended period, if any, not exceeding three months in the aggregate,`
  line `as the Registrar may allow, applies to the Registrar for directions with respect to the advertisement of the`
  line `assignment, and advertises it in such form and manner and within such period as the Registrar may direct.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, an assignment of a trade mark of the following`
  line `description shall not be deemed to be an assignment made otherwise than in connection with the goodwill`
  line `of the business in which the mark is used, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) an assignment of a trade mark in respect only of some of the goods or services for which the`
  line `trade mark is registered accompanied by the transfer of the goodwill of the business concerned in`
  line `those goods or services only; or`
  line
  line `(b) an assignment of a trade mark which is used in relation to goods exported from India or in`
  line `relation to services for use outside India if the assignment is accompanied by the transfer of the`
  line `goodwill of the export business only.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (16835)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 50
  title `Assignability and transmissibility of certification trade marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16835&sectionno=43&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `A certification trade mark`
  line `shall not be assignable or transmissible otherwise than with the consent of the Registrar, for which`
  line `application shall be made in writing in the prescribed manner.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (16836)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 51
  title `Assignability and transmissibility of associated trade marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16836&sectionno=44&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `Associated trade marks shall`
  line `be assignable and transmissible only as a whole and not separately, but, subject to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, they shall, for all other purposes, be deemed to have been registered as separate trade mark.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (16837)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 52
  title `Registration of assignments and transmissions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 40 of 2010, s. 6, for section 45 (w.e.f. 8-7-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16837&sectionno=45&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `^1[45. Registration of assignments and transmissions.--(1) Where a person becomes entitled by`
  line `assignment or transmission to a registered trade mark, he shall apply in the prescribed manner to the`
  line `Registrar to register his title, and the Registrar shall, on receipt of the application, register him as the`
  line `proprietor of the trade mark in respect of the goods or services in respect of which the assignment or`
  line `transmission has effect, and shall cause particulars of such assignment or transmission to be entered on`
  line `the register.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar may require the applicant to furnish evidence or further evidence in proof of title`
  line `only where there is a reasonable doubt about the veracity of any statement or any document furnished.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the validity of an assignment or transmission is in dispute between the parties, the`
  line `Registrar may refuse to register the assignment or transmission until the rights of the parties have been`
  line `determined by a competent court and in all other cases the Registrar shall dispose of the application`
  line `within the prescribed period.`
  line
  line `(4) Until an application under sub-section (1) has been filed, the assignment or transmission shall be`
  line `ineffective against a person acquiring a conflicting interest in or under the registered trade mark without`
  line `the knowledge of assignment or transmission.]`
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (16838)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 53
  title `Proposed use of trade mark by company to be formed, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes `1.Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 21, for “tribunal” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16838&sectionno=46&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) No application for the`
  line `registration of a trade mark in respect of any goods or services shall be refused nor shall permission for`
  line `such registration be withheld, on the ground only that it appears that the applicant does not use or propose`
  line `to use the trade mark if the Registrar is satisfied that--`
  line
  line `(a) a company is about to be formed and registered under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)`
  line `and that the applicant intends to assign the trade mark to that company with a view to the use thereof`
  line `in relation to those goods or services by the company, or`
  line
  line `(b) the proprietor intends it to be used by a person, as a registered user after the registration of the`
  line `trade mark.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of section 47 shall have effect, in relation to a trade mark registered under the`
  line `powers conferred by this sub-section, as if for the reference, in clause (a) of sub-section (1) of that`
  line `section, to the intention on the part of an applicant for registration that a trade mark should be used by`
  line `him there were substituted a reference to the intention on his part that it should be used by the company or`
  line `registered user concerned.`
  line
  line `(3) The ^1[Registrar or the High Court, as the case may be,] may, in a case to which sub-section (1) applies, require the applicant to give security`
  line `for the costs of any proceedings relating to any opposition or appeal, and in default of such security being`
  line `duly given, may treat the application as abandoned.`
  line
  line `(4) Where in a case to which sub-section (1) applies, a trade mark in respect of any goods or services`
  line `is registered in the name of an applicant who, relies on intention to assign the trade mark to a company,`
  line `then, unless within such period as may be prescribed or within such further period not exceeding six`
  line `months as the Registrar may, on application being made to him in the prescribed manner, allow, the`
  line `company has been registered as the proprietor of the trade mark in respect of those goods or services, the`
  line `registration shall cease to have effect in respect thereof at the expiration of that period and the Registrar`
  line `shall amend the register accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (16839)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 54
  title `Removal from register and imposition of limitations on ground of non-use.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16839&sectionno=47&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) A registered`
  line `trade mark may be taken off the register in respect of the goods or services in respect of which it is registered on application made in the prescribed manner to the Registrar or the ^1[High Court] by any`
  line `person aggrieved on the ground either--`
  line
  line `(a) that the trade mark was registered without any bona fide intention on the part of the applicant`
  line `for registration that it should be used in relation to those goods or services by him or, in a case to`
  line `which the provisions of section 46 apply, by the company concerned or the registered user, as the case`
  line `may be, and that there has, in fact, been no bona fide use of the trade mark in relation to those goods`
  line `or services by any proprietor thereof for the time being up to a date three months before the date of`
  line `the application; or`
  line
  line `(b) that up to a date three months before the date of the application, a continuous period of five`
  line `years from the date on which the trade mark is actually entered in the register or longer had elapsed`
  line `during which the trade mark was registered and during which there was no bona fide use thereof in`
  line `relation to those goods or services by any proprietor thereof for the time being:`
  line
  line `Provided that except where the applicant has been permitted under section 12 to register an identical`
  line `or nearly resembling trade mark in respect of the goods or services in question, or where the ^2[Registrar or the High Court, as the case may be] is of`
  line `opinion that he might properly be permitted so to register such a trade mark, the ^2[Registrar or`
  line `the High Court, as the case may be] may refuse an`
  line `application under clause (a) or clause (b) in relation to any goods or services, if it is shown that there has`
  line `been, before the relevant date or during the relevant period, as the case may be, bona fide use of the trade`
  line `mark by any proprietor thereof for the time being in relation to--`
  line
  line `(i) goods or services of the same description; or`
  line
  line `(ii) goods or services associated with those goods or services of that description being goods or`
  line `services, as the case may be, in respect of which the trade mark is registered.`
  line
  line `(2) Where in relation to any goods or services in respect of which a trade mark is registered--`
  line
  line `(a) the circumstances referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (1) are shown to exist so far as`
  line `regards non-use of the trade mark in relation to goods to be sold, or otherwise traded in a particular`
  line `place in India (otherwise than for export from India), or in relation to goods to be exported to a`
  line `particular market outside India; or in relation to services for use or available for acceptance in a`
  line `particular place in India or for use in a particular market outside India; and`
  line
  line `(b) a person has been permitted under section 12 to register an identical or nearly resembling`
  line `trade mark in respect of those goods, under a registration extending to use in relation to goods to be`
  line `so sold, or otherwise traded in, or in relation to goods to be so exported, or in relation to services for`
  line `use or available for acceptance in that place or for use in that country, or the tribunal is of opinion that`
  line `he might properly be permitted so to register such a trade mark,`
  line
  line `on application by that person in the prescribed manner to the ^1[High Court] or to the Registrar, the`
  line `tribunal may impose on the registration of the first-mentioned trade mark such limitations as it thinks`
  line `proper for securing that that registration shall cease to extend to such use.`
  line
  line `(3) An applicant shall not be entitled to rely for the purpose of clause (b) of sub-section (1) or for the`
  line `purposes of sub-section (2) on any non-use of a trade mark which is shown to have been due to special`
  line `circumstances in the trade, which includes restrictions on the use of the trade mark in India imposed by`
  line `any law or regulation and not to any intention to abandon or not to use the trade mark in relation to the`
  line `goods or services to which the application relates.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for “Appellate Board” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 21, for “tribunal” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (16840)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 55
  title `Registered users.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16840&sectionno=48&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of section 49, a person other than the registered`
  line `proprietor of a trade mark may be registered as a registered user thereof in respect of any or all of the`
  line `goods or services in respect of which the trade mark is registered.`
  line
  line `(2) The permitted use of a trade mark shall be deemed to be used by the proprietor thereof, and shall`
  line `be deemed not to be used by a person other than the proprietor, for the purposes of section 47 or for any`
  line `other purpose for which such use is material under this Act or any other law.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (16841)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 56
  title `Registration as registered user.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16841&sectionno=49&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where it is proposed that a person should be registered as`
  line `a registered user of a trade mark, the registered proprietor and the proposed registered user shall jointly apply in writing to the Registrar in the prescribed manner, and every such application shall be`
  line `accompanied by--`
  line
  line `(a) the agreement in writing or a duly authenticated copy thereof, entered into between the`
  line `registered proprietor and the proposed registered user with respect to the permitted use of the trade`
  line `mark; and`
  line
  line `(b) an affidavit made by the registered proprietor or by some person authorised to the satisfication`
  line `of the Registrar to act on his behalf,--`
  line
  line `(i) giving particulars of the relationship, existing or proposed, between the registered`
  line `proprietor and the proposed registered user, including particulars showing the degree of control`
  line `by the proprietor over the permitted use which their relationship will confer and whether it is a`
  line `term of their relationship that the proposed registered user shall be the sole registered user or that`
  line `there shall be any other restriction as to persons for whose registration as registered users`
  line `application may be made;`
  line
  line `(ii) stating the goods or services in respect of which registration is proposed;`
  line
  line `(iii) stating the conditions or restrictions, if any, proposed with respect to the characteristics`
  line `of the goods or services, to the mode or place of permitted use, or to any other matter;`
  line
  line `(iv) stating whether the permitted use is to be for a period or without limit of period, and, if`
  line `for a period, the duration thereof; and`
  line
  line `(c) such further documents or other evidence as may be required by the Registrar or as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) When the requirements of sub-section (1) have been complied with, the Registrar shall register the`
  line `proposed registered user in respect of the goods or services as to which he is so satisfied.`
  line
  line `(3) The Registrar shall issue notice in the prescribed manner of the registration of a person as a`
  line `registered user, to other registered users of the trade mark, if any.`
  line
  line `(4) The Registrar shall, if so requested by the applicant, take steps for securing that information given`
  line `for the purposes of an application under this section (other than matters entered in the register) is not`
  line `disclosed to rivals in trade.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (16842)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 57
  title `Power of Registrar for variation or cancellation of registration as registered user.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16842&sectionno=50&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Without prejudice to the provisions of section 57, the registration of a person as registered user--`
  line
  line `(a) may be varied by the Registrar as regards the goods or services in respect of which it has`
  line `effect on the application in writing in the prescribed manner of the registered proprietor of the trade`
  line mark;
  line
  line `(b) may be cancelled by the Registrar on the application in writing in the prescribed manner of`
  line `the registered proprietor or of the registered user or of any other registered user of the trade mark;`
  line
  line `(c) may be cancelled by the Registrar on the application in writing in the prescribed manner of`
  line `any person on any of the following grounds, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) that the registered user has used the trade mark otherwise than in accordance with the`
  line `agreement under clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 49 or in such way as to cause or to be`
  line `likely to cause, deception or confusion;`
  line
  line `(ii) that the proprietor or the registered user misrepresented, or failed to disclose, some fact`
  line `material to the application for registration which if accurately represented or disclosed would not`
  line `have justified the registration of the registered user;`
  line
  line `(iii) that the circumstances have changed since the date of registration in such a way that at`
  line `the date of such application for cancellation they would not have justified registration of the`
  line `registered user;`
  line
  line `(iv) that the registration ought not to have been effected having regard to rights vested in the`
  line `applicant by virtue of a contract in the performance of which he is interested;`
  line
  line `(d) may be cancelled by the Registrar on his own motion or on the application in writing in the`
  line `prescribed manner by any person, on the ground that any stipulation in the agreement between the`
  line `registered proprietor and the registered user regarding the quality of the goods or services in relation`
  line `to which the trade mark is to be used is either not being enforced or is not being complied with;`
  line
  line `(e) may be cancelled by the Registrar in respect of any goods or services in relation to which the`
  line `trade mark is no longer registered.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar shall issue notice in the prescribed manner in respect of every application under this`
  line `section to the registered proprietor and each registered user (not being the applicant) of the trade mark.`
  line
  line `(3) The procedure for cancelling a registration shall be such as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that before cancelling of registration, the registered proprietor shall be given a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (16843)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 58
  title `Power of Registrar to call for information relating to agreement in respect of registered users.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16843&sectionno=51&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Registrar may, at any time during the continuance of the registration of the registered`
  line `user, by notice in writing, require the registered proprietor to confirm to him within one month that the`
  line `agreement filed under clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 49 continues to be in force.`
  line
  line `(2) If the registered proprietor fails to furnish the confirmation within one month as required under`
  line `sub-section (1), the registered user shall cease to be the registered user on the day immediately after the`
  line `expiry of the said period and the Registrar shall notify the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (16844)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 59
  title `Right of registered user to take proceedings against infringement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16844&sectionno=52&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to any`
  line `agreement subsisting between the parties, a registered user may institute proceedings for infringement in`
  line `his own name as if he were the registered proprietor, making the registered proprietor a defendant and the`
  line `rights and obligations of such registered user in such case being concurrent with those of the registered`
  line proprietor.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law, a registered proprietor so added as`
  line `defendant shall not be liable for any costs unless he enters an appearance and takes part in the`
  line proceedings.
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (16845)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 60
  title `No right of permitted user to take proceeding against infringement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16845&sectionno=53&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `A person referred to in`
  line `sub-clause (ii) of clause (r) of sub-section (1) of section 2 shall have no right to institute any proceeding`
  line `for any infringement.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (16846)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 61
  title `Registered user not to have right of assignment or transmission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16846&sectionno=54&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall`
  line `confer on a registered user of a trade mark any assignable or transmissible right to the use thereof.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.--The right of a registered user of a trade mark shall not be deemed to have been`
  line `assigned or transmitted within the meaning of this section in the following cases, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) where the registered user being an individual enters into a partnership with any other person`
  line `for carrying on the business concerned; but in any such case the firm may use the trade mark, if`
  line `otherwise in force, only for so long as the registered user is a member of the firm;`
  line
  line `(b) where the registered user being a firm subsequently undergoes a change in its constitution; but`
  line `in any such case the reconstituted firm may use the trade mark, if otherwise in force, only for so long`
  line `as any partner of the original firm at the time of its registration as registered user, continues to be a`
  line `partner of the reconstituted firm.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.--For the purposes of Explanation I, "firm" has the same meaning as in the Indian`
  line `Partnership Act, 1932 (9 of 1932).`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (16847)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 62
  title `Use of one of associated or substantially identical trade marks equivalent to use of another.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 21, for “tribunal” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16847&sectionno=55&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where under the provisions of this Act, use of a registered trade mark is required to be`
  line `proved for any purpose, the ^1[Registrar or the High Court, as the case may be,] may, if and, so far as it shall think right, accept use of a registered`
  line `associated trade mark, or of the trade mark with additions or alterations not substantially affecting its`
  line `identity, as an equivalent for the use required to be proved.`
  line
  line `(2) The use of the whole of a registered trade mark shall, for the purpose of this Act, be deemed to be`
  line `also use of any trade mark being a part thereof and registered in accordance with sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 15 in the name of the same proprietor.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything in section 32, the use of part of the registered trade mark in`
  line `sub-section (2) shall not be conclusive as to its evidence of distinctiveness for any purpose under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (16848)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 63
  title `Use of trade mark for export trade and use when form of trade connection changes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16848&sectionno=56&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `The application in India of trade mark to goods to be exported from India or in relation to services for use`
  line `outside India and any other act done in India in relation to goods to be so exported or services so rendered`
  line `outside India which, if done in relation to goods to be sold or services provided or otherwise traded in`
  line `within India would constitute use of a trade mark therein, shall be deemed to constitute use of the trade`
  line `mark in relation to those goods or services for any purpose for which such use is material under this Act`
  line `or any other law.`
  line
  line `(2) The use of a registered trade mark in relation to goods or services between which and the person`
  line `using the mark any form of connection in the course of trade subsists shall not be deemed to be likely to`
  line `cause deception or confusion on the ground only that the mark has been or is used in relation to goods or`
  line `services between which and the said person or a predecessor in title of that person a different form of`
  line `connection in the course of trade subsisted or subsists.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (16849)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 64
  title `Power to cancel or vary registration and to rectify the register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16849&sectionno=57&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) On application made in`
  line `the prescribed manner to the ^1[High Court] or to the Registrar by any person aggrieved, the ^2[Register or the High`
  line `Court, as the case may be,]`
  line `may make such order as it may think fit for cancelling or varying the registration of a trade mark on the`
  line `ground of any contravention, or failure to observe a condition entered on the register in relation thereto.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person aggrieved by the absence or omission from the register of any entry, or by any entry`
  line `made in the register without sufficient cause, or by any entry wrongly remaining on the register, or by any`
  line `error or defect in any entry in the register, may apply in the prescribed manner to the ^1[High Court] or`
  line `to the Registrar, and the ^2[Register or the High`
  line `Court, as the case may be,] may make such order for making, expunging or varying the entry as it`
  line `may think fit.`
  line
  line `(3) The ^2[Register or the High`
  line `Court, as the case may be,] may in any proceeding under this section decide any question that may be necessary`
  line `or expedient to decide in connection with the rectification of the register.`
  line
  line `(4) The ^2[Register or the High`
  line `Court, as the case may be,], of its own motion, may, after giving notice in the prescribed manner to the parties`
  line `concerned and after giving them an opportunity of being heard, make any order referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) or sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(5) Any order of the ^1[High Court] rectifying the register shall direct that notice of the rectification`
  line `shall be served upon the Registrar in the prescribed manner who shall upon receipt of such notice rectify`
  line `the register accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for “Appellate Board” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for “tribunal” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (16850)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 65
  title `Correction of register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16850&sectionno=58&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Registrar may, on application made in the prescribed manner`
  line `by the registered proprietor,--`
  line
  line `(a) correct any error in the name, address or description of the registered proprietor of a trade`
  line `mark, or any other entry relating to the trade mark;`
  line
  line `(b) enter any change in the name, address or description of the person who is registered as`
  line `proprietor of a trade mark;`
  line
  line `(c) cancel the entry of a trade mark on the register;`
  line
  line `(d) strike out any goods or classes of goods or services from those in respect of which a trade`
  line `mark is registered,`
  line
  line `and may make any consequential amendment or alteration in the certificate of registration, and for that`
  line `purpose, may require the certificate of registration to be produced to him.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar may, on application made in the prescribed manner by a registered user of a trade`
  line `mark, and after notice to the registered proprietor, correct any error, or enter any change, in the name,`
  line `address or description of the registered user.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (16851)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 66
  title `Alteration of registered trade marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16851&sectionno=59&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) The registered proprietor of a trade mark may apply`
  line `in the prescribed manner to the Registrar for leave to add to or alter the trade mark in any manner not`
  line `substantially affecting the identity thereof, and the Registrar may refuse leave or may grant it on such`
  line `terms and subject to such limitations as he may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar may cause an application under this section to be advertised in the prescribed`
  line `manner in any case where it appears to him that it is expedient so to do, and where he does so, if within`
  line `the prescribed time from the date of the advertisement any person gives notice to the Registrar in the`
  line `prescribed manner of opposition to the application, the Registrar shall, after hearing the parties if so`
  line `required, decide the matter.`
  line
  line `(3) Where leave is granted under this section, the trade mark as altered shall be advertised in the`
  line `prescribed manner, unless the application has already been advertised under sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (16852)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 67
  title `Adaptation of entries in register to amended or substituted classification of goods or services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16852&sectionno=60&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Registrar shall not make any amendment of the register which would have the effect`
  line `of adding any goods or classes of goods or services to those in respect of which a trade mark is registered`
  line `(whether in one or more classes) immediately before the amendment is to be made or of antedating the`
  line `registration of a trade mark in respect of any goods or services:`
  line
  line `Provided that this sub-section, shall not apply when the Registrar is satisfied that compliance`
  line `therewith would involve undue complexity and that the addition or antedating, as the case may be, would`
  line `not affect any substantial quantity of goods or services and would not substantially prejudice the rights of`
  line `any person.`
  line
  line `(2) A proposal so to amend the register shall be brought to the notice of the registered proprietor of`
  line `the trade mark affected and advertised in the prescribed manner, and may be opposed before the Registrar`
  line `by any person aggrieved on the ground that the proposed amendment contravenes the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (16853)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 68
  title `Special provisions for collective marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16853&sectionno=61&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this Act shall apply to collective`
  line `marks subject to the provisions contained in this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) In relation to a collective mark the reference in clause (zb) of sub-section (1) of section 2 to`
  line `distinguishing the goods or services of one person from those of others shall be construed as a reference`
  line `to distinguishing the goods or services of members of an association of persons which is the proprietor of`
  line `the mark from those of others.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (16854)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 69
  title `Collective mark not to be misleading as to character or significance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16854&sectionno=62&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `A collective mark shall`
  line `not be registered if it is likely to deceive or cause confusion on the part of public in particular if it is likely`
  line `to be taken to be something other than a collective mark, and in such case the Registrar may require that a`
  line `mark in respect of which application is made for registration comprise some indication that it is a`
  line `collective mark.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (16855)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 70
  title `Application to be accompanied by regulations governing use of collective marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16855&sectionno=63&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `(1) An`
  line `application for registration of a collective mark shall be accompanied by the regulations governing the use`
  line `of such collective mark.`
  line
  line `(2) The regulations referred to in sub-section (1) shall specify the persons authorised to use the mark,`
  line `the conditions of membership of the association and, the conditions of use of the mark, including any`
  line `sanctions against misuse and such other matters as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (16856)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 71
  title `Acceptance of application and regulations by Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16856&sectionno=64&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `If it appears to the Registrar that the`
  line `requirements for registration are satisfied, he shall accept the application together with the regulations, either unconditionally or subject to such conditions including amendments of the said regulations, if any,`
  line `as he may deem fit or refuse to accept it and if accepted shall notify the regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (16857)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 72
  title `Regulations to be open to inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16857&sectionno=65&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `The regulations referred to in sub-section (1) of section`
  line `63 shall be open to public inspection in the same way as the register as provided in section 148.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (16858)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 73
  title `Amendment of regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16858&sectionno=66&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `Any amendment of regulations referred to in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 63 shall not be effective unless the amended regulations are filed with the Registrar, and accepted`
  line `and published by him in accordance with section 64.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (16859)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 74
  title `Infringement proceedings by registered proprietor of collective mark.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16859&sectionno=67&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `In a suit for`
  line `infringement instituted by the registered proprietor of a collective mark as plaintiff the court shall take`
  line `into account any loss suffered or likely to be suffered by authorised users and may give such directions as`
  line `it thinks fit as to the extent to which the plaintiff shall hold the proceeds of any pecuniary remedy on`
  line `behalf of such authorised users.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (16860)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 75
  title `Additional grounds for removal of registration of collective mark.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16860&sectionno=68&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `The registration of a`
  line `collective mark may also be removed from the register on the ground--`
  line
  line `(a) that the manner in which the collective mark has been used by the proprietor or authorised`
  line `user has caused it to become liable to mislead the public as a collective mark; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the proprietor has failed to observe, or to secure the observance of the regulations`
  line `governing the use of the mark.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.--For the purposes of this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires, "authorised`
  line `user" means a member of an association authorised to use the registered collective mark of the`
  line association.
  line
  line `Explanation II.--For the purposes of this Act, use of a collective mark by an authorised user referred`
  line `to in Explanation I shall be deemed to be the use by the registered proprietor thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (16861)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 76
  title `Certain provisions of this Act not applicable to certification trade marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16861&sectionno=69&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `The following`
  line `provisions of this Act shall not apply to certification trade marks, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) clauses (a) and (c) of sub-section (1) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(b) Sections 18, 20 and 21, except as expressly applied by this Chapter;`
  line
  line `(c) Sections 28, 29, 30, 41, 42, 47, 48, 49, 50, 52, 54 and sub-section (2) of section 56;`
  line
  line `(d) Chapter XII, except section 107.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (16862)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 77
  title `Registration of certification trade marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16862&sectionno=70&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `A mark shall not be registrable as a certification`
  line `trade mark in the name of a person who carries on a trade in goods of the kind certified or a trade of the`
  line `provision of services of the kind certified.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (16863)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 78
  title `Applications for registration of certification trade marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 21, for “tribunal” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16863&sectionno=71&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `(1) An application for the`
  line `registration of a mark as a certification trade mark shall be made to the Registrar in the prescribed manner`
  line `by the person proposed to be registered as the proprietor thereof, and accompanied by a draft for the`
  line `regulations to be deposited under section 74.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of section 70, the provisions of sections 18, 19 and 22 shall apply in`
  line `relation to an application under this section as they apply in relation to an application under section 18,`
  line `subject to the modification that references therein to acceptance of an application shall be construed as`
  line `references to authorisation to proceed with an application.`
  line
  line `(3) In dealing under the said provisions with an application under this section, the ^1[Registrar or the`
  line `High Court, as the case may be,] shall have`
  line `regard to the like considerations, so far as relevant, as if the application were applications under section`
  line `18 and to any other considerations relevant to applications under this section, including the desirability of`
  line `securing that a certification trade mark shall comprise some indication that it is a certification trade mark.`
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (16864)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 79
  title `Consideration of application for registration by Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16864&sectionno=72&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Registrar shall consider`
  line `the application made under section 71 with regard to the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) whether the applicant is competent to certify the goods in respect of which the mark is to be`
  line registered;
  line
  line `(b) whether the draft of the regulations to be filed under section 74 is satisfactory;`
  line
  line `(c) whether in all the circumstances the registration applied for would be to the public advantage,`
  line
  line `and may either--`
  line
  line `(i) refuse the application; or`
  line
  line `(ii) accept the application and approve the said draft of the regulations either without modification`
  line `and unconditionally or subject to any conditions or limitations, or to any amendments or`
  line `modifications of the application or of the regulations, which he thinks requisite having regard to any`
  line `of the said matters.`
  line
  line `(2) Except in the case of acceptance and approval without modification and unconditionally, the`
  line `Registrar shall not decide any matter under sub-section (1) without giving the applicant an opportunity of`
  line `being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (16865)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 80
  title `Opposition to registration of certification trade marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16865&sectionno=73&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `When an application has been`
  line `accepted, the Registrar shall, as soon as may be thereafter, cause the application as accepted to be`
  line `advertised in the prescribed manner, and the provisions of section 21 shall apply in relation to the`
  line `registration of the mark as they apply in relation to an application under section 18.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (16866)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 81
  title `Filing of regulations governing use of a certification trade mark.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16866&sectionno=74&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be filed at`
  line `the Trade Marks Registry in respect of every mark registered as a certification trade mark regulations for`
  line `governing the use thereof, which shall include provisions as to the cases in which the proprietor is to`
  line `certify goods or services and to authorise the use of the certification trade mark, and may contain any`
  line `other provisions which the Registrar may by general or special order, require or permit to be inserted`
  line `therein (including provisions conferring a right of appeal to the Registrar against any refusal of the`
  line `proprietor to certify goods or to authorise the use of the certification trade mark in accordance with the`
  line `regulations); and regulations so filed shall be open to inspection in like manner as the register as provided`
  line `in section 148.`
  line
  line `(2) The regulations so filed may, on the application of the registered proprietor, be altered by the`
  line Registrar.
  line
  line `(3) The Registrar may cause such application to be advertised in any case where it appears to him`
  line `expedient so to do, and where he does so, if within the time specified in the advertisement any person`
  line `gives notice of opposition to the application, the Registrar shall not decide the matter without giving the`
  line `parties an opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (16867)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 82
  title `Infringement of certification trade marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16867&sectionno=75&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `The right conferred by section 78 is infringed by`
  line `any person who, not being the registered proprietor of the certification trade mark or a person authorised`
  line `by him in that behalf under the regulations filed under section 74, using it in accordance therewith, uses in`
  line `the course of trade, a mark, which is identical with, or deceptively similar to the certification trade mark`
  line `in relation to any goods or services in respect of which it is registered, and in such manner as to render the`
  line `use of the mark likely to be taken as being a use as a trade mark.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (16868)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 83
  title `Acts not constituting infringement of certification trade marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16868&sectionno=76&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Act, the following acts do not constitute an infringement of the right to the use`
  line `of a registered certification trade mark--`
  line
  line `(a) where a certification trade mark is registered subject to any conditions or limitations entered`
  line `on the register, the use of any such mark in any mode, in relation to goods to be sold or otherwise`
  line `traded in any place, or in relation to goods to be exported to any market or in relation to services for`
  line `use or available for acceptance in any place, country or territory or in any other circumstances, to`
  line `which having regard to any such limitations, the registration does not extend;`
  line
  line `(b) the use of a certification trade mark in relation to goods or services certified by the proprietor`
  line `of the mark if, as to those goods or services or a bulk of which they form part, the proprietor or another in accordance with his authorisation under the relevant regulations has applied the mark and`
  line `has not subsequently removed or obliterated it, or the proprietor has at any time expressly or`
  line `impliedly consented to the use of the mark;`
  line
  line `(c) the use of a certification trade mark in relation to goods or services adapted to form part of, or`
  line `to be accessory to, other goods in relation to which the mark has been used without infringement of`
  line `the right given as aforesaid or might for the time being be so used, if the use of the mark is reasonably`
  line `necessary in order to indicate that the goods or services are so adapted and neither the purpose nor the`
  line `effect of the use of the mark is to indicate otherwise than in accordance with the fact that the goods or`
  line `services are certified by the proprietor.`
  line
  line `(2) Clause (b) of sub-section (1) shall not apply to the case of use consisting of the application of a`
  line `certification trade mark to goods or services, notwithstanding that they are such goods or services as are`
  line `mentioned in that clause if such application is contrary to the regulations referred to in that clause.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a certification trade mark is one of two or more trade marks registered under this Act,`
  line `which are identical or nearly resemble each other, the use of any of those trade marks in exercise of the`
  line `right to the use of that trade mark given by registration, shall not be deemed to be an infringement of the`
  line `right so given to the use of any other of those trade marks.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (16869)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 84
  title `Cancellation or varying of registration of certification trade marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16869&sectionno=77&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `The Registrar may, on`
  line `the application in the prescribed manner of any person aggrieved and after giving the proprietor an`
  line `opportunity of opposing the application, make such order as he thinks fit for expunging or varying any`
  line `entry in the register to a certification trade mark, or for varying the regulations, on any of the following`
  line `grounds, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) that the proprietor is no longer competent, in the case of any of the goods or services in`
  line `respect of which the mark is registered, to certify those goods or services;`
  line
  line `(b) that the proprietor has failed to observe any provisions of the regulations to be observed on his`
  line part;
  line
  line `(c) that it is no longer to the public advantage that the mark should remain registered;`
  line
  line `(d) that it is requisite for the public advantage that if the mark remains registered, the regulations`
  line `should be varied.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (16870)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 85
  title `Rights conferred by registration of certification trade marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16870&sectionno=78&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions`
  line `of sections 34, 35 and 76, the registration of a person as a proprietor of certification trade mark in respect`
  line `of any goods or services shall, if valid, give to that person the exclusive right to the use of the mark in`
  line `relation to those goods or services.`
  line
  line `(2) The exclusive right to the use of a certification trade mark given under sub-section (1) shall be`
  line `subject to any conditions and limitations to which the registration is subject.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
