obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (16893)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 109
  title `Meaning of applying trade marks and trade descriptions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16893&sectionno=101&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall be deemed to`
  line `apply a trade mark or mark or trade description to goods or services who--`
  line
  line `(a) applies it to the goods themselves or uses it in relation to services; or`
  line
  line `(b) applies it to any package in or with which the goods are sold, or exposed for sale, or had in`
  line `possession for sale or for any purpose of trade or manufacture; or`
  line
  line `(c) places, encloses or annexes any goods which are sold, or exposed for sale, or had in`
  line `possession for sale or for any purpose of trade or manufacture, in or with any package or other thing`
  line `to which a trade mark or mark or trade description has been applied; or`
  line
  line `(d) uses a trade mark or mark or trade description in any manner reasonably likely to lead to the`
  line `belief that the goods or services in connection with which it is used are designated or described by`
  line `that trade mark or mark or trade description; or`
  line
  line `(e) in relation to the goods or services uses a trade mark or trade description in any sign,`
  line `advertisement, invoice, catalogue, business letter, business paper, price list or other commercial`
  line `document and goods are delivered or services are rendered to a person in pursuance of a request or`
  line `order made by reference to the trade mark or trade description as so used.`
  line
  line `(2) A trade mark or mark or trade description shall be deemed to be applied to goods whether it is`
  line `woven in, impressed on, or otherwise worked into, or annexed or affixed to, the goods or to any package`
  line `or other thing.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (16894)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 110
  title `Falsifying and falsely applying trade marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16894&sectionno=102&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall be deemed to falsify a trade`
  line `mark who, either,--`
  line
  line `(a) without the assent of the proprietor of the trade mark makes that trade mark or a deceptively`
  line `similar mark; or`
  line
  line `(b) falsifies any genuine trade mark, whether by alteration, addition, effacement or otherwise.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall be deemed to falsely apply to goods or services a trade mark who, without the`
  line `assent of the proprietor of the trade mark,--`
  line
  line `(a) applies such trade mark or a deceptively similar mark to goods or services or any package`
  line `containing goods;`
  line
  line `(b) uses any package bearing a mark which is identical with or deceptively similar to the trade`
  line `mark of such proprietor, for the purpose of packing, filling or wrapping therein any goods other than`
  line `the genuine goods of the proprietor of the trade mark.`
  line
  line `(3) Any trade mark falsified as mentioned in sub-section (1) or falsely applied as mentioned in`
  line `sub-section (2), is in this Act referred to as a false trade mark.`
  line
  line `(4) In any prosecution for falsifying a trade mark or falsely applying a trade mark to goods or`
  line `services, the burden of proving the assent of the proprietor shall lie on the accused.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (16895)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 111
  title `Penalty for applying false trade marks, trade descriptions, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16895&sectionno=103&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `Any person who--`
  line
  line `(a) falsifies any trade mark; or`
  line
  line `(b) falsely applies to goods or services any trade mark; or`
  line
  line `(c) makes, disposes of, or has in his possession, any die, block, machine, plate or other instrument`
  line `for the purpose of falsifying or of being used for falsifying, a trade mark; or`
  line
  line `(d) applies any false trade description to goods or services; or`
  line
  line `(e) applies to any goods to which an indication of the country or place in which they were made`
  line `or produced or the name and address of the manufacturer or person for whom the goods are`
  line `manufactured is required to be applied under section 139, a false indication of such country, place,`
  line `name or address; or`
  line
  line `(f) tampers with, alters or effaces an indication of origin which has been applied to any goods to`
  line `which it is required to be applied under section 139; or`
  line
  line `(g) causes any of the things above mentioned in this section to be done,`
  line
  line `shall, unless he proves that he acted, without intent to defraud, be punishable with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which shall not be less than six months but which may extend to three years and with fine which`
  line `shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees but which may extend to two lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for adequate and special reasons to be mentioned in the judgment,`
  line `impose a sentence of imprisonment for a term of less than six months or a fine of less than fifty thousand`
  line rupees.
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (16896)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 112
  title `Penalty for selling goods or providing services to which false trade mark or false trade description is applied.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16896&sectionno=104&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `Any person who sells, lets for hire or exposes for sale, or hires or has in his`
  line `possession for sale, goods or things, or provides or hires services, to which any false trade mark or false`
  line `trade description is applied or which, being required under section 139 to have applied to them an`
  line `indication of the country or place in which they were made or produced or the name and address of the`
  line `manufacturer, or person for whom the goods are manufactured or services provided, as the case may be,`
  line `are without the indications so required, shall, unless he proves,--`
  line
  line `(a) that, having taken all reasonable precautions against committing an offence against this`
  line `section, he had at the time of commission of the alleged offence no reason to suspect the genuineness of the trade mark or trade description or that any offence had been committed in respect of the goods`
  line `or services; or`
  line
  line `(b) that, on demand by or on behalf of the prosecutor, he gave all the information in his power`
  line `with respect to the person from whom he obtained such goods or things or services; or`
  line
  line `(c) that otherwise he had acted innocently,`
  line
  line `be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six months but which may`
  line `extend to three years and with fine which shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees but which may`
  line `extend to two lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for adequate and special reasons to be mentioned in the judgment,`
  line `impose a sentence of imprisonment for a term of less than six months or a fine of less than fifty thousand`
  line rupees.
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (16897)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 113
  title `Enhanced penalty on second or subsequent conviction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16897&sectionno=105&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `Whoever having already been convicted`
  line `of an offence under section 103 or section 104 is again convicted of any such offence shall be punishable`
  line `for the second and for every subsequent offence, with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less`
  line `than one year but which may extend to three years and with fine which shall not be less than one lakh`
  line `rupees but which may extend to two lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for adequate and special reason to be mentioned in the judgement,`
  line `impose a sentence of imprisonment for a term of less than one year or a fine of less than one lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided further that for the purposes of this section, no cognizance shall be taken of any conviction`
  line `made before the commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (16898)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 114
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
