obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (16902)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 118
  title `No offence in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16902&sectionno=110&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of sections 102, 103, 104 and 105 shall, in`
  line `relation to a registered trade mark or proprietor of such mark, be subject to the rights created or`
  line `recognised by this Act and no act or omission shall be deemed to be an offence under the aforesaid`
  line `sections if,--`
  line
  line `(a) the alleged offence relates to a registered trade mark and the act or omission is permitted`
  line `under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(b) the alleged offence relates to a registered or an unregistered trade mark and the act or`
  line `omission is permitted under any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (16903)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 119
  title `Forfeiture of goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16903&sectionno=111&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a person is convicted of an offence under section 103 or`
  line `section 104 or section 105 or is acquitted of an offence under section 103 or section 104 on proof that he`
  line `acted without intent to defraud, or under section 104 on proof of the matters specified in clause (a),`
  line `clause (b) or clause (c) of that section, the court convicting or acquitting him may direct the forfeiture to`
  line `Government of all goods and things by means of, or in relation to, which the offence has been committed,`
  line `or but for such proof as aforesaid would have been committed.`
  line
  line `(2) When a forfeiture is directed on a conviction and an appeal lies against the conviction, an appeal`
  line `shall lie against the forfeiture also.`
  line
  line `(3) When a forfeiture is directed on acquittal and the goods or things to which the direction relates are`
  line `of value exceeding fifty rupees, an appeal against the forfeiture may be preferred, within thirty days from`
  line `the date of the direction, to the court to which in appealable cases appeals lie from sentences of the court`
  line `which directed the forfeiture.`
  line
  line `(4) When a forfeiture is directed on a conviction, the court, before whom the person is convicted, may`
  line `order any forfeited articles to be destroyed or otherwise disposed of as the court thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (16904)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 120
  title `Exemption of certain persons employed in ordinary course of business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16904&sectionno=112&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `Where a person`
  line `accused of an offence under section 103 proves--`
  line
  line `(a) that in the ordinary course of his business he is employed on behalf of other persons to apply`
  line `trade marks or trade descriptions, or as the case may be, to make dies, blocks, machines, plates, or`
  line `other instruments for making, or being used in making, trade marks; and`
  line
  line `(b) that in the case which is the subject of the charge he was so employed, and was not interested`
  line `in the goods or other thing by way of profit or commission dependent on the sale of such goods or`
  line `providing of services, as the case may be; and`
  line
  line `(c) that, having taken all reasonable precautions against committing the offence charged, he had,`
  line `at the time of the commission of the alleged offence, no reason to suspect the genuineness of the trade`
  line `mark or trade description; and`
  line
  line `(d) that, on demand made by or on behalf of the prosecutor, he gave all the information in his`
  line `power with respect to the persons on whose behalf the trade mark or trade description was applied,`
  line
  line `he shall be acquitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112_a:
  sectionId (93232)
  sectionNo 112A
  orderNo 121
  title `Adjudication of penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 1-8-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=93232&sectionno=112A&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_112_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[112A. Adjudication of penalties.— The Registrar may, by an order, authorise an officer referred to`
  line `in section 3, to be adjudicating officer for holding an inquiry and imposing penalty under the provisions`
  line `of this Act, in the manner as may be prescribed, after giving a reasonable opportunity of being heard.]`
obj_root_law_sections_112_b:
  sectionId (93233)
  sectionNo 112B
  orderNo 122
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 1-8-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=93233&sectionno=112B&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_112_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[112B. Appeal.—(1) Whoever aggrieved by an order of the adjudicating officer under section 112A`
  line `may prefer an appeal to the appellate authority, who shall be an officer at least one rank above the`
  line `adjudicating officer, within a period of sixty days from the date of receipt of the order, as the Central`
  line `Government may by notification authorise in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal under this section shall be preferred in such form and manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) An appeal may be admitted after the expiry of the period of sixty days if the appellant satisfies the`
  line `appellate authority that he had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within that period.`
  line
  line `(4) No appeal shall be disposed of unless the appellant has been given a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `being heard.`
  line
  line `(5) The appellate authority referred to in sub-section (1) shall dispose of the appeal within sixty days`
  line `from the date of filing.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, if the person fails to comply with the order of the`
  line `adjudicating officer under section 112A or the order of the appellate authority under this section, as the`
  line `case may be, within ninety days of such order, he shall, in addition to the penalty, be punishable with fine`
  line `of one lakh rupees or imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (16905)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 123
  title `Procedure where invalidity of registration is pleaded by the accused.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16905&sectionno=113&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the`
  line `offence charged under section 103 or section 104 or section 105 is in relation to a registered trade mark`
  line `and the accused pleads that the registration of the trade mark is invalid, the following procedure shall be`
  line `followed:--`
  line
  line `(a) If the court is satisfied that such defence is prima facie tenable, it shall not proceed with the`
  line `charge but shall adjourn the proceeding for three months from the date on which the plea of the`
  line `accused is recorded to enable the accused to file an application before the ^1[High Court] under this`
  line `Act, for the rectification of the register on the ground that the registration is invalid.`
  line
  line `(b) If the accused proves to the court that he has made such application within the time so limited`
  line `or within such further time as the court may for sufficient cause allow, the further proceedings in the`
  line `prosecution shall stand stayed till the disposal of such application for rectification.`
  line
  line `(c) If within a period of three months or within such extended time as may be allowed by the`
  line `court the accused fails to apply to the ^1[High Court] for rectification of the register, the court shall`
  line `proceed with the case as if the registration were valid.`
  line
  line `(2) Where before the institution of a complaint of an offence referred to in sub-section (1), any`
  line `application for the rectification of the register concerning the trade mark in question on the ground of`
  line `invalidity of the registration thereof has already been properly made to and is pending before the ^2[Registrar or the High Court, as the case may be,]`
  line `the court shall stay the further proceedings in the prosecution pending the disposal of the application`
  line `aforesaid and shall determine the charge against the accused in conformity with the result of the`
  line `application for rectification in so far as the complainant relies upon the registration of his mark.`
obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 21, for “Appellate Board” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for “tribunal” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (16906)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 124
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16906&sectionno=114&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the person committing an offence under this Act is a company,`
  line `the company as well as every person in charge of, and responsible to, the company for the conduct of its`
  line `business at the time of the commission of the offence shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall`
  line `be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he exercised all`
  line `due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or that the commission of the offence is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any`
  line `director, manager, secretary or other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and`
  line `punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_115:
  sectionId (16907)
  sectionNo (115)
  orderNo 125
  title `Cognizance of certain offences and the powers of police officer for search and seizure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_115_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16907&sectionno=115&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_115_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `No court shall take cognizance of an offence under section 107 or section 108 or section 109 except on`
  line `complaint in writing made by the Registrar or any officer authorised by him in writing:`
  line
  line `Provided that in relation to clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 107, a court shall take cognizance`
  line `of an offence on the basis of a certificate issued by the Registrar to the effect that a registered trade mark`
  line `has been represented as registered in respect of any goods or services in respect of which it is not in fact`
  line registered.
  line
  line `(2) No court inferior to that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or Judicial Magistrate of the first class shall`
  line `try an offence under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The offences under section 103 or section 104 or section 105 shall be cognizable.`
  line
  line `(4) Any police officer not below the rank of deputy superintendent of police or equivalent, may, if he`
  line `is satisfied that any of the offences referred to in sub-section (3) has been, is being, or is likely to be,`
  line `committed, search and seize without warrant the goods, die, block, machine, plate, other instruments or`
  line `things involved in committing the offence, wherever found, and all the articles so seized shall, as soon as`
  line `practicable, be produced before a Judicial Magistrate of the first class or Metropolitan Magistrate, as the`
  line `case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that the police officer, before making any search and seizure, shall obtain the opinion of the`
  line `Registrar on facts involved in the offence relating to trade mark and shall abide by the opinion so`
  line obtained.
  line
  line `(5) Any person having an interest in any article seized under sub-section (4), may, within fifteen days`
  line `of such seizure, make an application to the Judicial Magistrate of the first class or Metropolitan`
  line `Magistrate, as the case may be, for such article being restored to him and the Magistrate, after hearing the`
  line `applicant and the prosecution, shall make such order on the application as he may deem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (16908)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 126
  title `Evidence of origin of goods imported by sea.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16908&sectionno=116&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `In the case of goods brought into India by sea,`
  line `evidence of the port of shipment shall, in a prosecution for an offence under this Act or under clause (b)`
  line `of section 112 of the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962) relating to confiscation of goods under clause (d) of`
  line `section 111 and notified by the Central Government under clause (n) of sub-section (2) of section 11 of`
  line `the said Act for the protection of trade marks relating to import of goods, be prima facie evidence of the`
  line `place or country in which the goods were made or produced.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_117:
  sectionId (16909)
  sectionNo (117)
  orderNo 127
  title `Costs of defence or prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16909&sectionno=117&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_117_content:
  string
  line `In any prosecution under this Act, the court may order such`
  line `costs to be paid by the accused to the complainant, or by the complainant to the accused, as the court`
  line `deems reasonable having regard to all the circumstances of the case and the conduct of the parties and the`
  line `costs so awarded shall be recoverable as if they were a fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_118:
  sectionId (16910)
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 128
  title `Limitation of prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16910&sectionno=118&orderno=128&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution for an offence under this Act or under clause (b)`
  line `of section 112 of the Customs Act,1962 (52 of 1962), relating to confiscation of goods under clause (d) of`
  line `section 111 and notified by the Central Government under clause (n) of sub-section (2) of section 11 of`
  line `the said Act for the protection of trade marks, relating to import of goods shall be commenced after`
  line `expiration of three years next after the commission of the offence charged, or two years after the`
  line `discovery thereof by the prosecutor, whichever expiration first-happens.`
obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_119:
  sectionId (16911)
  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 129
  title `Information as to commission of offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16911&sectionno=119&orderno=129&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line `An officer of the Government whose duty it is to`
  line `take part in the enforcement of the provisions of this Chapter shall not be compelled in any court to say`
  line `whence he got any information as to the commission of any offence against this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_120:
  sectionId (16912)
  sectionNo (120)
  orderNo 130
  title `Punishment of abetment in India of acts done out of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_120_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16912&sectionno=120&orderno=130&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line `If any person, being within`
  line `India, abets the commission, without India, of any act which, if committed in India, would, under this`
  line `Act, be an offence, he may be tried for such abetment in any place in India in which he may be found, and`
  line `be punished therefor with the punishment to which he would be liable if he had himself committed in that`
  line `place the act which he abetted.`
obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_121:
  sectionId (16913)
  sectionNo (121)
  orderNo 131
  title `Instructions of Central Government as to permissible variation to be observed by criminal courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_121_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16913&sectionno=121&orderno=131&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, issue instructions for the`
  line `limits of variation, as regards number, quantity, measure, gauge or weight which are to be recognised by`
  line `criminal courts as permissible in the case of any goods.`
obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (16914)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 132
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16914&sectionno=122&orderno=132&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceedings shall lie against`
  line `any person in respect of anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (16915)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 133
  title `Certain persons to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes `1. The words “and every Member of the Appellate Board” omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 21 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16915&sectionno=123&orderno=133&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line `Every person appointed under this Act ^1*** shall be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of section 21`
  line `of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_124:
  sectionId (16916)
  sectionNo (124)
  orderNo 134
  title `Stay of proceedings where the validity of registration of the trade mark is questioned, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 21, for “Appellate Board” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16916&sectionno=124&orderno=134&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where in any suit for infringement of a trade mark--`
  line
  line `(a) the defendant pleads that registration of the plaintiff's trade mark is invalid; or`
  line
  line `(b) the defendant raises a defence under clause (e) of sub-section (2) of section 30 and the`
  line `plaintiff pleads the invalidity of registration of the defendants trade mark,`
  line
  line `the court trying the suit (hereinafter referred to as the court), shall,--`
  line
  line `(i) if any proceedings for rectification of the register in relation to the plaintiff's or defendant's`
  line `trade mark are pending before the Registrar or the ^1[High Court], stay the suit pending the final`
  line `disposal of such proceedings;`
  line
  line `(ii) if no such proceedings are pending and the court is satisfied that the plea regarding the`
  line `invalidity of the registration of the plaintiff's or defendant's trade mark is prima facie tenable, raise`
  line `an issue regarding the same and adjourn the case for a period of three months from the date of the`
  line `framing of the issue in order to enable the party concerned to apply to the ^1[High Court] for`
  line `rectification of the register.`
  line
  line `(2) If the party concerned proves to the court that he has made any such application as is referred to in`
  line `clause (b) (ii) of sub-section (1) within the time specified therein or within such extended time as the`
  line `court may for sufficient cause allow, the trial of the suit shall stand stayed until the final disposal of the`
  line `rectification proceedings.`
  line
  line `(3) If no such application as aforesaid has been made within the time so specified or within such`
  line `extended time as the court may allow, the issue as to the validity of the registration of the trade mark`
  line `concerned shall be deemed to have been abandoned and the court shall proceed with the suit in regard to`
  line `the other issues in the case.`
  line
  line `(4) The final order made in any rectification proceedings referred to in sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (2) shall be binding upon the parties and the court shall dispose of the suit conformably to`
  line `such order in so far as it relates to the issue as to the validity of the registration of the trade mark.`
  line
  line `(5) The stay of a suit for the infringement of a trade mark under this section shall not preclude the`
  line `court from making any interlocutory order (including any order granting an injunction, directing account`
  line `to be kept, appointing a receiver or attaching any property), during the period of the stay of the suit.`
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (16917)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 135
  title `Application for rectification of register to be made to High Court in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 21, for “Appellate Board” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16917&sectionno=125&orderno=135&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where in a suit for infringement of a registered trade mark the validity of the registration of`
  line `the plaintiff's trade mark is questioned by the defendant or where in any such suit the defendant raises a`
  line `defence under clause (e) of sub-section (2) of section 30 and the plaintiff questions the validity of the`
  line `registration of the defendant's trade mark, the issue as to the validity of the registration of the trade mark`
  line `concerned shall be determined only on an application for the rectification of the register and,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in section 47 or section 57, such application shall be made to the`
  line `^1[High Court] and not the Registrar.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1), where an application for rectification of the register is`
  line `made to the Registrar under section 47 or section 57, the Registrar may, if he thinks fit, refer the`
  line `application at any stage of the proceedings to the ^1[High Court].`
obj_root_law_sections_126:
  sectionId (16918)
  sectionNo (126)
  orderNo 136
  title `Implied warranty on sale of marked goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16918&sectionno=126&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_126_content:
  string
  line `Where a mark or a trade mark or trade`
  line `description has been applied to the goods on sale or in the contract for sale of any goods or in relation to`
  line `any service, the seller shall be deemed to warrant that the mark is a genuine mark and not falsely applied,`
  line `or that the trade description is not a false trade description within the meaning of this Act unless the`
  line `contrary is expressed in writing signed by or on behalf of the seller and delivered at the time of the sale of`
  line `goods or providing of services on contract to and accepted by the buyer.`
obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127:
  sectionId (16919)
  sectionNo (127)
  orderNo 137
  title `Powers of Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16919&sectionno=127&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_127_content:
  string
  line `In all proceedings under this Act before the Registrar,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Registrar shall have all the powers of a civil court for the purposes of receiving evidence,`
  line `administering oaths, enforcing the attendance of witnesses, compelling the discovery and production`
  line `of documents and issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses;`
  line
  line `(b) the Registrar may, subject to any rules made in this behalf under section 157, make such`
  line `orders as to costs as he considers reasonable, and any such order shall be executable as a decree of a`
  line `civil court:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Registrar shall have no power to award costs to or against any party on an`
  line `appeal to him against a refusal of the proprietor of a certification trade mark to certify goods or`
  line `provision of services or to authorise the use of the mark;`
  line
  line `(c) the Registrar may, on an application made in the prescribed manner, review his own decision.`
obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_128:
  sectionId (16920)
  sectionNo (128)
  orderNo 138
  title `Exercise of discretionary power by Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16920&sectionno=128&orderno=138&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 131, the`
  line `Registrar shall not exercise any discretionary or other power vested to him by this Act or the rules made`
  line `thereunder adversely to a person applying for the exercise of that power without (if so required by that`
  line `person within the prescribed time) giving to the person an opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_129:
  sectionId (16921)
  sectionNo (129)
  orderNo 139
  title `Evidence before Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16921&sectionno=129&orderno=139&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line `In any proceeding under this Act before the Registrar, evidence`
  line `shall be given by affidavit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Registrar may, if he thinks fit, take oral evidence in lieu of, or in addition to, such`
  line `evidence by affidavit.`
obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_130:
  sectionId (16922)
  sectionNo (130)
  orderNo 140
  title `Death of party to a proceeding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_content
  footnotes `1. The words “the Appellate Board or” omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 21 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16922&sectionno=130&orderno=140&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_130_content:
  string
  line `If a person who is a party to a proceeding under this Act (not`
  line `being a proceeding before ^1*** or a court) dies pending the proceeding, the Registrar may,`
  line `on request, and on proof to his satisfaction of the transmission of the interest of the deceased person,`
  line `substitute in the proceeding his successor in interest in his place, or, if the Registrar is of opinion that the`
  line `interest of the deceased person is sufficiently represented by the surviving parties, permit the proceeding`
  line `to continue without the substitution of his successor in interest.`
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  sectionId (16923)
  sectionNo (131)
  orderNo 141
  title `Extension of time.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16923&sectionno=131&orderno=141&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_131_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Registrar is satisfied, on application made to him in the`
  line `prescribed manner and accompanied by the prescribed fee, that there is sufficient cause for extending the`
  line `time for doing any act (not being a time expressly provided in this Act), whether the time so specified has`
  line `expired or not, he may, subject to such conditions as he may think fit to impose, extend the time and`
  line `inform the parties accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall be deemed to require the Registrar to hear the parties before`
  line `disposing of an application for extension of time, and no appeal shall lie from any order of the Registrar`
  line `under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_132:
  sectionId (16924)
  sectionNo (132)
  orderNo 142
  title Abandonment.
  content obj_root_law_sections_132_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16924&sectionno=132&orderno=142&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_132_content:
  string
  line `Where, in the opinion of the Registrar, an applicant is in default in the`
  line `prosecution of an application filed under this Act or any Act relating to trade marks in force prior to the`
  line `commencement of this Act, the Registrar may, by notice require the applicant to remedy the default`
  line `within a time specified and after giving him, if so, desired, an opportunity of being heard, treat the`
  line `application as abandoned, unless the default is remedied within the time specified in the notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_133:
  sectionId (16925)
  sectionNo (133)
  orderNo 143
  title `Preliminary advice by the Registrar as to distinctiveness.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_133_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16925&sectionno=133&orderno=143&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_133_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Registrar may, on`
  line `application made to him in the prescribed manner by any person who proposes to apply for the`
  line `registration of a trade mark, give advice as to whether the trade mark appears to him prima facie to be`
  line distinctive.
  line
  line `(2) If, on an application for the registration of a trade mark as to which the Registrar has given advice`
  line `as aforesaid in the affirmative made within three months after the advice was given, the Registrar, after`
  line `further investigation or consideration, gives notice, to the applicant of objection on the ground that the`
  line `trade mark is not distinctive, the applicant shall be entitled, on giving notice of withdrawal of the`
  line `application within the prescribed period, to have repaid to him any fee paid on the filing of the`
  line application.
obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_134:
  sectionId (16926)
  sectionNo (134)
  orderNo 144
  title `Suit for infringement, etc., to be instituted before District Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16926&sectionno=134&orderno=144&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_134_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit--`
  line
  line `(a) for the infringement of a registered trade mark; or`
  line
  line `(b) relating to any right in a registered trade mark; or`
  line
  line `(c) for passing off arising out of the use by the defendant of any trade mark which is identical`
  line `with or deceptively similar to the plaintiff's trade mark, whether registered or unregistered,`
  line `shall be instituted in any court inferior to a District Court having jurisdiction to try the suit.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of clauses (a) and (b) of sub-section (1), a "District Court having jurisdiction"`
  line `shall, notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) or any other`
  line `law for the time being in force, include a District Court within the local limits of whose jurisdiction, at the`
  line `time of the institution of the suit or other proceeding, the person instituting the suit or proceeding, or,`
  line `where there are more than one such persons any of them, actually and voluntarily resides or carries on`
  line `business or personally works for gain.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of sub-section (2), "person" includes the registered proprietor and`
  line `the registered user.`
obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_135:
  sectionId (16927)
  sectionNo (135)
  orderNo 145
  title `Relief in suits for infringement or for passing off.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16927&sectionno=135&orderno=145&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line `(1) The relief which a court may grant in`
  line `any suit for infringement or for passing off referred to in section 134 includes injunction (subject to such`
  line `terms, if any, as the court thinks fit) and at the option of the plaintiff, either damages or an account of`
  line `profits, together with or without any order for the delivery-up of the infringing labels and marks for`
  line `destruction or erasure.`
  line
  line `(2) The order of injunction under sub-section (1) may include an ex parte injunction or any`
  line `interlocutory order for any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) for discovery of documents;`
  line
  line `(b) preserving of infringing goods, documents or other evidence which are related to the`
  line `subject-matter of the suit;`
  line
  line `(c) restraining the defendant from disposing of or dealing with his assets in a manner which may`
  line `adversely affect plaintiff's ability to recover damages, costs or other pecuniary remedies which may`
  line `be finally awarded to the plaintiff.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the court shall not grant relief by way of`
  line `damages (other than nominal damages) or on account of profits in any case--`
  line
  line `(a) where in a suit for infringement of a trade mark, the infringement complained of is in relation`
  line `to a certification trade mark or collective mark; or`
  line
  line `(b) where in a suit for infringement the defendant satisfies the court--`
  line
  line `(i) that at the time he commenced to use the trade mark complained of in the suit, he was`
  line `unaware and had no reasonable ground for believing that the trade mark of the plaintiff was on`
  line `the register or that the plaintiff was a registered user using by way of permitted use; and`
  line
  line `(ii) that when he became aware of the existence and nature of the plaintiff's right in the trade`
  line `mark, he forthwith ceased to use the trade mark in relation to goods or services in respect of`
  line `which it was registered; or`
  line
  line `(c) where in a suit for passing off, the defendant satisfies the court--`
  line
  line `(i) that at the time he commenced to use the trade mark complained of in the suit, he was`
  line `unaware and had no reasonable ground for believing that the trade mark for the plaintiff was in`
  line `use; and`
  line
  line `(ii) that when he became aware of the existence and nature of the plaintiff's trade mark he`
  line `forthwith ceased to use the trade mark complained of.`
obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  sectionId (16928)
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 146
  title `Registered user to be impleaded in certain proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16928&sectionno=136&orderno=146&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line `(1) In every proceeding under`
  line `chapter VII or under section 91, every registered user of a trade mark using by way of permitted use, who`
  line `is not himself an applicant in respect of any proceeding under that Chapter or section, shall be made a`
  line `party to the proceeding.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law, a registered user so made a party to the`
  line `proceeding shall not be liable for any costs unless he enters an appearance and takes part in the`
  line proceeding.
obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_137:
  sectionId (16929)
  sectionNo (137)
  orderNo 147
  title `Evidence of entries in register, etc., and things done by the Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_137_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16929&sectionno=137&orderno=147&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_137_content:
  string
  line `(1) A copy of any`
  line `entry in the register or of any document referred to in sub-section (1) of section 148 purporting to be certified by the Registrar and sealed with the seal of the Trade Marks Registry shall be admitted in`
  line `evidence in all courts and in all proceedings without further proof or production of the original.`
  line
  line `(2) A certificate purporting to be under the hand of the Registrar as to any entry, matter or thing that`
  line `he is authorised by this Act or the rules to make or do shall be prima facie evidence of the entry having`
  line `been made, and of the contents thereof, or of the matter or things having been done or not done.`
obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_138:
  sectionId (16930)
  sectionNo (138)
  orderNo 148
  title `Registrar and other officers not compellable to produce register, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16930&sectionno=138&orderno=148&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_138_content:
  string
  line `The Registrar or any`
  line `officer of the Trade Marks Registry shall not, in any legal proceedings to which he is not a party, be`
  line `compellable to produce the register or any other document in his custody, the contents of which can be`
  line `proved by the production of a certified copy issued under this Act or to appear as a witness to prove the`
  line `matters therein recorded unless by order of the court made for special cause.`
obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_139:
  sectionId (16931)
  sectionNo (139)
  orderNo 149
  title `Power to require goods to show indication of origin.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_139_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16931&sectionno=139&orderno=149&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_139_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, require that goods of any class specified in the notification which are`
  line `made or produced beyond the limits of India and imported into India, or, which are made or produced`
  line `within the limits of India, shall, from such date as may be appointed by the notification not being less than`
  line `three months from its issue, have applied to them an indication of the country or place in which they were`
  line `made or produced, or of the name and address of the manufacturer or the person for whom the goods were`
  line manufactured.
  line
  line `(2) The notification may specify the manner in which such indication shall be applied that is to say,`
  line `whether to goods themselves or in any other manner, and the times or occasions on which the presence of`
  line `the indication shall be necessary, that is to say, whether on importation only, or also at the time of sale,`
  line `whether by wholesale or retail or both.`
  line
  line `(3) No notification under this section shall be issued, unless application is made for its issue by`
  line `persons or associations substantially representing the interests of dealers in, or manufacturers, producers,`
  line `or users of, the goods concerned, or unless the Central Government is otherwise convinced that it is`
  line `necessary in the public interest to issue the notification, with or without such inquiry, as the Central`
  line `Government may consider necessary.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of section 23 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897) shall apply to the`
  line `issue of a notification under this section as they apply to the making of a rule or bye-law the making of`
  line `which is subject to the condition of previous publication.`
  line
  line `(5) A notification under this section shall not apply to goods made or produced beyond the limits of`
  line `India and imported into India, if in respect of those goods, the Commissioner of Customs is satisfied at`
  line `the time of importation that they are intended for exportation whether after transshipment in or transit`
  line `through India or otherwise.`
obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_140:
  sectionId (16932)
  sectionNo (140)
  orderNo 150
  title `Power to require information of imported goods bearing false trade marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_140_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 1-8-2024)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16932&sectionno=140&orderno=150&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_140_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `proprietor or a licensee of a registered trade mark may give notice in writing to the Collector of Customs`
  line `to prohibit the importation of any goods if the import of the said goods constitute infringement under`
  line `clause (c) of sub-section (6) of section 29.`
  line
  line `(2) Where goods, which are prohibited to be imported into India by notification of the Central`
  line `Government under clause (n) of sub-section (2) of section 11 of the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962), for`
  line `the protection of trade marks, and are liable to confiscation on importation under that Act, are imported`
  line `into India, the Commissioner of Customs if, upon representation made to him, he has reason to believe`
  line `that the trade mark complained of is used as a false trade mark, may require the importer of the goods, or`
  line `his agent, to produce any documents in his possession relating to the goods and to furnish information as`
  line `to the name and address of the person by whom the goods were consigned to India and the name and`
  line `address of the person to whom the goods were sent in India.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) The importer or his agent shall, within fourteen days, comply with the requirement as aforesaid,`
  line `and if he fails to do so, he shall be liable to penalty of ten thousand rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the penalty under this section shall be levied and recovered by such authority under the`
  line `Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962) for this purpose.]`
  line
  line `(4) Any information obtained from the importer of the goods or his agent under this section may be`
  line `communicated by the Commissioner of Customs to the registered proprietor or registered user of the trade`
  line `mark which is alleged to have been used as a false trade mark.`
obj_root_law_sections_141:
  sectionId (16933)
  sectionNo (141)
  orderNo 151
  title `Certificate of validity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_141_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 21, for “Appellate Board” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16933&sectionno=141&orderno=151&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_141_content:
  string
  line `If in any legal proceeding for rectification of the register before the`
  line `^1[High Court] a decision is on contest given in favour of the registered proprietor of the trade mark on`
  line `the issue as to the validity of the registration of the trade mark, the ^1[High Court] may grant a`
  line `certificate to that effect, and if such a certificate is granted, then, in any subsequent legal proceeding in`
  line `which the said validity comes into question the said proprietor on obtaining a final order or judgment in`
  line `his favour affirming validity of the registration of the trade mark shall, unless the said final order or`
  line `judgment for sufficient reason directs otherwise, be entitled to his full cost charges and expenses as`
  line `between legal practitioner and client.`
obj_root_law_sections_142:
  sectionId (16934)
  sectionNo (142)
  orderNo 152
  title `Groundless threats of legal proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_142_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16934&sectionno=142&orderno=152&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_142_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a person, by means of circulars,`
  line `advertisements or otherwise, threatens a person with an action or proceeding for infringement of a trade`
  line `mark which is registered, or alleged by the first-mentioned person to be registered, or with some other`
  line `like proceeding, a person aggrieved may, whether the person making the threats is or is not the registered`
  line `proprietor or the registered user of the trade mark, bring a suit against the first-mentioned person and may`
  line `obtain a declaration to the effect that the threats are unjustifiable, and an injunction against the`
  line `continuance of the threats and may recover such damages (if any) as he has sustained, unless the`
  line `first-mentioned person satisfies the court that the trade mark is registered and that the acts in respect of`
  line `which the proceedings were threatened, constitute, or, if done, would constitute, an infringement of the`
  line `trade mark.`
  line
  line `(2) The last preceding sub-section does not apply if the registered proprietor of the trade mark, or a`
  line `registered user acting in pursuance of sub-section (1) of section 52 with due diligence commences and`
  line `prosecutes an action against the person threatened for infringement of the trade mark.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall render a legal practitioner or a registered trade marks agent liable to`
  line `an action under this section in respect of an act done by him in his professional capacity on behalf of a`
  line client.
  line
  line `(4) A suit under sub-section (1) shall not be instituted in any court inferior to a District Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_143:
  sectionId (16935)
  sectionNo (143)
  orderNo 153
  title `Address for service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_143_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16935&sectionno=143&orderno=153&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_143_content:
  string
  line `An address for service stated in an application or notice of opposition`
  line `shall for the purposes of the application or notice of opposition be deemed to be the address of the`
  line `applicant or opponent, as the case may be, and all documents in relation to the application or notice of`
  line `opposition may be served by leaving them at or sending them by post to the address for service of the`
  line `applicant or opponent, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_144:
  sectionId (16936)
  sectionNo (144)
  orderNo 154
  title `Trade usages, etc., to be taken into consideration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_144_content
  footnotes `1.Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for “tribunal” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16936&sectionno=144&orderno=154&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_144_content:
  string
  line `In any proceeding relating to a trade`
  line `mark, the ^1[Registrar or the High Court, as the case may be,] shall admit evidence of the usages of the trade concerned and of any relevant trade`
  line `mark or trade name or get up legitimately used by other persons.`
obj_root_law_sections_145:
  sectionId (16937)
  sectionNo (145)
  orderNo 155
  title Agents.
  content obj_root_law_sections_145_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16937&sectionno=145&orderno=155&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_145_content:
  string
  line `Where, by or under this Act, any act, other than the making of an affidavit, is required`
  line `to be done before the Registrar by any person, the act may, subject to the rules made in this behalf, be`
  line `done instead of by that person himself, by a person duly authorised in the prescribed manner, who is--`
  line
  line `(a) a legal practitioner, or`
  line
  line `(b) a person registered in the prescribed manner as a trade marks agent, or`
  line
  line `(c) a person in the sole and regular employment of the principal.`
obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_146:
  sectionId (16938)
  sectionNo (146)
  orderNo 156
  title `Marks registered by an agent or representative without authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16938&sectionno=146&orderno=156&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_146_content:
  string
  line `If an agent or a`
  line `representative of the proprietor of a registered trade mark, without authority uses or attempts to register or`
  line `registers the mark in his own name, the proprietor shall be entitled to oppose the registration applied for`
  line `or secure its cancellation or rectification of the register so as to bring him as the registered proprietor of`
  line `the said mark by assignment in his favour:`
  line
  line `Provided that such action shall be taken within three years of the registered proprietor of the trade`
  line `mark becoming aware of the conduct of the agent or representative.`
obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_147:
  sectionId (16939)
  sectionNo (147)
  orderNo 157
  title Indexes.
  content obj_root_law_sections_147_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16939&sectionno=147&orderno=157&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_147_content:
  string
  line `There shall be kept under the direction and supervision of the Registrar--`
  line
  line `(a) an index of registered trade marks;`
  line
  line `(b) an index of trade marks in respect of which applications for registration are pending;`
  line
  line `(c) an index of the names of the proprietors of registered trade marks; and`
  line
  line `(d) an index of the names of registered users.`
obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_148:
  sectionId (16940)
  sectionNo (148)
  orderNo 158
  title `Documents open to public inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_148_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16940&sectionno=148&orderno=158&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_148_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 49,--`
  line
  line `(a) the register and any document upon which any entry in the register is based;`
  line
  line `(b) every notice of opposition to the registration of a trade mark application for rectification`
  line `before the Registrar, counter-statement thereto, and any affidavit or document filed by the parties in`
  line `any proceedings before the Registrar;`
  line
  line `(c) all regulations deposited under section 63 or section 74, and all applications under section 66`
  line `or section 77 for varying such regulations;`
  line
  line `(d) the indexes mentioned in section 147; and`
  line
  line `(e) such other documents as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line specify,
  line
  line `shall, subject to such conditions as may be prescribed, be open to public inspection at the Trade Marks`
  line `Registry:`
  line
  line `Provided that when such register is maintained wholly or partly on computer, the inspection of such`
  line `register under this section shall be made by inspecting the computer printout of the relevant entry in the`
  line `register so maintained on computer.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person may, on an application to the Registrar and on payment of such fees as may be`
  line `prescribed, obtain a certified copy of any entry in the register or any document referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_149:
  sectionId (16941)
  sectionNo (149)
  orderNo 159
  title `Reports of Registrar to be placed before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_149_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16941&sectionno=149&orderno=159&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_149_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall cause`
  line `to be placed before both Houses of Parliament once a year a report respecting the execution by or under`
  line `the Registrar of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_150:
  sectionId (16942)
  sectionNo (150)
  orderNo 160
  title `Fees and surcharge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_150_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 40 of 2010, s. 8, for "applications" (w.e.f. 8-7-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16942&sectionno=150&orderno=160&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_150_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be paid in respect of ^1[applications, international`
  line `applications] and registration and other matters under this Act such fees and surcharge as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a fee is payable in respect of the doing of an act by the Registrar, the Registrar shall not do`
  line `that act until the fee has been paid.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a fee is payable in respect of the filing of a document at the Trade Marks Registry, the`
  line `document shall be deemed not to have been filed at the Registry until the fee has been paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_151:
  sectionId (16943)
  sectionNo (151)
  orderNo 161
  title `Savings in respect of certain matters in Chapter XII.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16943&sectionno=151&orderno=161&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_151_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in Chapter XII shall--`
  line
  line `(a) exempt any person from any suit or other proceeding which might, but for anything in that`
  line `Chapter, be brought against him; or`
  line
  line `(b) entitle any person to refuse to make a complete discovery, or to answer any question or`
  line `interrogatory in any suit or other proceeding, but such discovery or answer shall not be admissible in`
  line `evidence against such person in any such prosecution for an offence under that Chapter or against`
  line `clause (h) of section 112 of the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962) relating to confiscation of goods`
  line `under clause (d) of section 111 of that Act and notified by the Central Government under clause (n) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 11 thereof for the protection of trade marks relating to import of goods; or`
  line
  line `(c) be construed so as to render liable to any prosecution or punishment any servant of a master`
  line `resident in India who in good faith acts in obedience to the instructions of such master, and, on`
  line `demand made by or on behalf of the prosecutor, has given full information as to his master and as to`
  line `the instructions which he has received from his master.`
obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_152:
  sectionId (16944)
  sectionNo (152)
  orderNo 162
  title `Declaration as to ownership of trade mark not registrable under the Registration Act, 1908.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_152_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16944&sectionno=152&orderno=162&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_152_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908), no`
  line `document declaring or purporting to declare the ownership or title of a person to a trade mark other than a`
  line `registered trade mark shall be registered under that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_153:
  sectionId (16945)
  sectionNo (153)
  orderNo 163
  title `Government to be bound.`
  content `The provisions of this Act shall be binding on the Government.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16945&sectionno=153&orderno=163&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_154:
  sectionId (16946)
  sectionNo (154)
  orderNo 164
  title `Special provisions relating to applications for registration from citizens of convention countries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_154_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16946&sectionno=154&orderno=164&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_154_content:
  string
  line `(1) With a view to the fulfilment of a treaty, convention or arrangement with any country or`
  line `country which is a member of a group of countries or union of countries or Inter-Governmental`
  line `Organisation outside India which affords to citizens of India similar privileges as granted to its own`
  line `citizens, the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare such country or`
  line `group of countries or union of countries or Inter-Governmental Organisation to be a convention country`
  line `or group of countries or union of countries or Inter-Governmental Organisation, as the case may be, for`
  line `the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a person has made an application for the registration of a trade mark in a convention`
  line `country or country which is a member of a group of countries or union of countries or Inter-Governmental`
  line `Organisation and that person, or his legal representative or assignee, makes an application for the`
  line `registration of the trade mark in India within six months after the date on which the application was made`
  line `in the convention country or country which is a member of a group of countries or union of countries or`
  line `Inter-Governmental Organisations, the trade mark shall, if registered under this Act, be registered as of`
  line `the date on which the application was made in the convention country or country which is a member of a`
  line `group of countries or union of countries or Inter-Governmental Organisation and that date shall be`
  line `deemed for the purposes of this Act to be the date of registration.`
  line
  line `(3) Where applications have been made for the registration of a trade mark in two or more convention`
  line `countries or country which are members of group of countries or union of countries or`
  line `Inter-Governmental Organisation, the period of six months referred to in the last preceding sub-section`
  line `shall be reckoned from the date on which the earlier or earliest of those applications was made.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in this Act shall entitle the proprietor of a trade mark to recover damages for infringement`
  line `which took place prior to the date of application for registration under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_155:
  sectionId (16947)
  sectionNo (155)
  orderNo 165
  title `Provision as to reciprocity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_155_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16947&sectionno=155&orderno=165&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_155_content:
  string
  line `Where any country or country which is a member of a group of`
  line `countries or union of countries or Inter-Governmental Organisation specified by the Central Government`
  line `in this behalf by notification in the Official Gazette does not accord to citizens of India the same rights in`
  line `respect of the registration and protection of trade marks as it accords to its own nationals, no national of`
  line `such country or country which is a member of a group of countries or union of countries or InterGovernmental`
  line `Organisation, as the case may be, shall be entitled, either solely or jointly with any other`
  line person,--
  line
  line `(a) to apply for the registration of, or be registered as the proprietor of, a trade mark;`
  line
  line `(b) to be registered as the assignee of the proprietor of a registered trade mark; or`
  line
  line `(c) to apply for registration or be registered as a registered user of a trade mark under section 49.`
obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_156:
  sectionId (16948)
  sectionNo (156)
  orderNo 166
  title `Power of Central Government to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_156_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16948&sectionno=156&orderno=166&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_156_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving`
  line `effect to the provisions of this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official`
  line `Gazette, make such provisions not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to be`
  line `necessary for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of five years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_157:
  sectionId (16949)
  sectionNo (157)
  orderNo 167
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_157_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16949&sectionno=157&orderno=167&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_157_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette and subject to the conditions of previous publication, make rules to carry out the provisions of`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(i) the matters to be included in the Register of Trade Marks under sub-section (1) of section 6,`
  line `and the safeguards to be observed in the maintenance of records on computer floppies or diskettes or`
  line `in any other electronic form under sub-section (2) of that section;`
  line
  line `(ii) the manner of publication of alphabetical index of classification of goods and services under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(iii) the manner in which the Registrar may notify a word as an international non-proprietary`
  line `name under section 13;`
  line
  line `(iv) the manner of making an application for dissolution of an association under sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 16;`
  line
  line `(v) the manner of making an application for registration of a trade mark under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 18;`
  line
  line `(vi) the manner of advertising of an application for registration under sub-section (1), and the`
  line `manner of notifying corrections or amendments under sub-section (2), of section 20;`
  line
  line `^1[(vii) the manner of giving a notice of opposition and the fee payable for such notice under`
  line `sub-section (1) and sending counter-statement under sub-section (2) and submission of evidence and`
  line `the time therefor under sub-section (4) of section 21;]`
  line
  line `(viii) the form of certificate of registration under sub-section (2), and the manner of giving notice`
  line `to the applicant under sub-section (3) of section 23;`
  line
  line `(ix) the forms of application for renewal and restoration the time within which such application is`
  line `to be made and fee and surcharge if any payable with each application, under section 25 and the time`
  line `within which the Registrar shall send a notice and the manner of such notice under`
  line `sub-section (3) of that section;`
  line
  line `^2[(ixa) the time within which the international application is to be forwarded to the International`
  line `Bureau and the manner of certifying the particulars by the Registrar under sub-section (4) of section`
  line 36D;
  line
  line `(ixb) the manner of keeping a record of particulars of an international registration under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 36E;]`
  line
  line `(ixc) the manner of informing the International Bureau under sub-section (2) of section 36E;`
  line
  line `(ixd) the manner of advertising the international registration and the time within which the`
  line `international registration shall be advertised under sub-section (3) of section 36E;]`
  line
  line `(x) the manner of submitting statement of cases under sub-section (2) of section 40;`
  line
  line `(xi) the manner of making an application by the proprietor of a trade mark under section 41;`
  line
  line `(xii) the manner of making an application for assignment or transmission of a certification trade`
  line `mark under section 43;`
  line
  line `(xiii) the manner of making an application to the Registrar to register title under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 45;`
  line
  line `^2[(xiiia) the period within which the Registrar shall dispose of an application under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 45;]`
  line
  line `(xiv) the manner in which and the period within which an application is to be made under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 46;`
  line
  line `(xv) the manner of making an application under sub-section (2) of section 47;`
  line
  line `(xvi) the manner of making an application, documents and other evidence to accompany such`
  line `application under sub-section (1) and the manner in which notice is to be issued under sub-section (3)`
  line `of section 49;`
  line
  line `(xvii) the manner of making an application under sub-section (1), the manner of issuing a notice`
  line `under sub-section (2) and the procedure for cancelling a registration under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 50;`
  line
  line `(xviii) the manner of making applications under sub-sections (1) and (2), the manner of giving`
  line `notice under sub-section (4) and the manner of service of notice of rectification under sub-section (5)`
  line `of section 57;`
  line
  line `(xix) the manner of making an application under section 58;`
  line
  line `(xx) the manner of making an application under sub-section (1), the manner of advertising an`
  line `application, time and manner of notice by which application may be opposed under sub-sections (2)`
  line `and (3) of section 59;`
  line
  line `(xxi) the manner of advertisement under sub-section (2) of section 60;`
  line
  line `(xxii) the other matters to be specified in the regulations under sub-section (2) of section 63;`
  line
  line `(xxiii) the manner of making an application under sub-section (1) of section 71;`
  line
  line `(xxiv) the manner of advertising an application under section 73;`
  line
  line `(xxv) the manner of making an application under section 77;`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(xxix) the salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `^4[Chairperson], ^5[Vice-Chairperson] and other Members under sub-section (1) of section 88;`
  line
  line `(xxx) the procedure for investigation of misbehavior or incapacity of the ^4[Chairperson],`
  line `^5[Vice-Chairperson] and other Members under sub-section (3) of section 89;`
  line
  line ^6*****
  line
  line `(xxxiii) the form in which and the particulars to be included in the application to the ^7[High Court] under sub-section (1) of section 97;`
  line
  line `^8[(xxxiiia) the manner of holding inquiry and imposing penalty under Section 112A;`
  line
  line `(xxxiiib) the form and manner of preferring appeal under sub-section (2) of Section 112B;]`
  line
  line `(xxxiv) the manner of making an application for review under clause (c) of section 127;`
  line
  line `(xxxv) the time within which an application is to be made to the Registrar for exercising his`
  line `discretionary power under section 128;`
  line
  line `(xxxvi) the manner of making an application and the fee payable therefor under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 131;`
  line
  line `(xxxvii) the manner of making an application under sub-section (1) and the period for withdrawal`
  line `of such application under sub-section (2) of section 133;`
  line
  line `(xxxviii) the manner of authorising any person to act and the manner of registration as a trade`
  line `mark agent under section 145;`
  line
  line `(xxxix) the conditions for inspection of documents under sub-section (1) and the fee payable for`
  line `obtaining a certified copy of any entry in the register under sub-section (2) of section 148;`
  line
  line `(xl) the fees and surcharge payable for making applications and registration and other matters`
  line `under section 150;`
  line
  line `(xli) any other matter which is required to be or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The power to make rules conferred by this section shall include the power to give retrospective`
  line `effect in respect of the matters referred to in clauses (xxix) and (xxxi) of sub-section (2) from a date not`
  line `earlier than the date of commencement of this Act, but no retrospective effect shall be given to any such`
  line `rule so as to prejudicially affect the interests of any person to whom sub-rule may be applicable.`
  line
  line `(4) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may`
  line `be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 40 of 2010, s. 9, for clause (vii) (w.e.f. 8-7-2013).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 8-7-2013).`
  line
  line `3. Cls. (xxvi), (xxvii) and (xxviii) omitted by Act 40 of 2010, s. 9 (w.e.f. 8-7-2013).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 161, for Chairman (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 161, ibid., for Vice-Chairman (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  line
  line `6. Clauses (xxxi) and (xxxii) omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 21 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `7.Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for Appellate Board (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 1-8-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_158:
  sectionId (16950)
