obj_root_law_sections_158_content:
  string
  line `The enactment specified in the Schedule shall be amended in the manner`
  line `specified therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_159:
  sectionId (16951)
  sectionNo (159)
  orderNo 169
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_159_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972&sectionId=16951&sectionno=159&orderno=169&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00004_199947_1517807323972
obj_root_law_sections_159_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Trade and Merchandise Marks Act, 1958 (43 of 1958) is hereby`
  line repealed.
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1987), with`
  line `respect to repeals, any notification, rule, order, requirement, registration, certificate, notice, decision,`
  line `determination, direction, approval, authorisation, consent, application, request or thing made, issued,`
  line `given or done under the Trade and Merchandise Marks Act, 1958 (43 of 1958) shall, if in force at the`
  line `commencement of this Act, continue to be in force and have effect as if made, issued, given or done under`
  line `the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of this Act shall apply to any application for registration of a trade mark pending at`
  line `the commencement of this Act and to any proceedings consequent thereon and to any registration granted`
  line `in pursuance thereof.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the provisions of section 100 and notwithstanding anything contained in any other`
  line `provision of this Act, any legal proceeding pending in any court at the commencement of this Act may be`
  line `continued in that court as if this Act had not been passed.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, where a particular use of a registered trade mark`
  line `is not an infringement of a trade mark registered before the commencement of this Act, then, the`
  line `continued use of that mark shall not be an infringement under this Act.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), the date of expiration of registration of a`
  line `trade mark registered before the commencement of this Act shall be the date immediately after the period`
  line `of seven years for which it was registered or renewed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the registration of a defensive trade mark referred to in section 47 of the Trade and`
  line `Merchandise Marks Act, 1958 (43 of 1958) shall cease to have effect on the date immediately after the`
  line `expiry of five years of such commencement or after the expiry of the period for which it was registered or`
  line `renewed, whichever is earlier.`
obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes:
  string
  line
